title: rum chocolate cake
directions: *If using cake mix with pudding already in mix; omit instant pudding, use only 3 eggs and only 1/3 cup oil.

title: crescent roll-ups
directions: Separate crescent rolls.
Add 1 slice of pepperoni and 1 slice of cheese.
Roll from wide end.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Brush each roll with beaten egg.
Bake as directed on package of crescent roll.
Makes 16 roll-ups.

title: quick tortoni cups
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Pile into 10 individual paper bake cups in muffin pans.
Freeze until firm.
Top each with a maraschino cherry flower.
Makes 10 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together.
Use juice from pineapple and mandarin oranges and mix with 2 packages instant vanilla pudding.
Add enough milk to make 3 cups.
Spoon on top of fruit and top with nuts.
(May substitute diet pudding.)

title: sunshine sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in small pan.
Heat until warmed through.
Serve over poached or broiled fillets.
(Diabetic cooking.)

title: san juan salad
directions: Combine vegetables, salt and pepper in salad bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, French dressing and horseradish in bowl. Add to salad; toss lightly to mix.
Chill until serving time. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: hot buttered pineapple drink
directions: Combine the half and half with the ginger ale and sprinkle with nutmeg. It's goooood!

title: frijole cheese soup
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, heat oil; add onions, pepper and garlic. Cook over medium flame until tender.
Add tomatoes with liquid, bacon and spices.
Stir; cook 5 minutes.
Add beans; increase heat to medium-high and cook until thoroughly heated.
Ladle into 2 bowls and top with mixed cheeses.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread cubes into a greased casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in the blender.
When blended, pour over the bread cubes and place in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes, peel and mash.
Cream eggs and sugar.
Add potatoes, margarine (melted), coconut and vanilla.
Pour into uncooked pie shells and cook at 375° until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine salad ingredients.
Toss with dressing which has been whisked together (oil, lime juice and spices).
Serve at room temperature.

title: grandmother's pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, eggs, vanilla, butter, sugar and salt.
When well blended, add pecans and pour into a 9-inch pastry.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish, layer cooked macaroni and grated cheese twice.
Place pats of margarine on top.
Pour milk over casserole.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer at medium speed until frothy. Gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Ad the next four ingredients; mix well.
Pour mixture into freezer can of 1-gallon freezer.
Add enough milk to fill can about 3/4 full.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
Let ripen at least 1 hour.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: cheez dypp
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Cut Velveeta into chunks and begin to melt.
Add all other ingredients to melting cheese.
Heat and stir until all cheese has melted.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown meat, drain and add Ro-Tel tomatoes, sour cream, garlic salt and melted cheese.

title: party franks
directions: Wrap
one strip of bacon around each frank half.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place	in
casserole
dish and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake until all of syrup is absorbed into franks, in a 300°
oven.
Turn
oven up to 350° for last 10 minutes to crisp bacon slightly.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken.
Chill broth and remove fat on surface.
Heat broth and add rice.
Saute onions and celery in separate skillet. When rice is done, add onions, celery, chili powder, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Debone chicken before serving.

title: grandma's osgood pies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture. Fill 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake about 1 hour at 300°.

title: raspberry sherbet
directions: Cook sugar and water in a pan for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly and add to gelatin.
Cool.
When mixture begins to congeal, add raspberries and put through food press.
Add fruit juice.
Pour into cold freezer tray and freeze for about 1-1/2 hours.
Remove sherbet to chilled bowl and beat for 2 minutes.
Return sherbet to tray and freeze about 2 to 3 hours.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: southern meat loaf
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients and 1/4 c. of the tomato sauce and gently mold into a loaf.	Pour the tomato sauce into a bowl.
Using the can as a measure, add the same amount of water. Mix in the prepared mustard.
Pour sauce over loaf and bake at 350° for one hour.	Yield: 6 servings.

title: citrus sunshine shake(two great "sunshine flavors" in this super shake.)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover; blend at medium speed for 30 seconds or until smooth and frothy.
Pour into glasses.
If desired, garnish with orange slice or pineapple wedge.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and roll into quarter-inch balls, then flatten out crisscross with fork, if wanted.
Put on greased cooking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and stir in the rest of the ingredients. Put all into a casserole dish and cover with the topping recipe.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Press into oblong pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
No icing.

title: peach whip
directions: Refrigerate can of peaches until very cold (2 to 3 hours). In heatproof measuring cup, combine gelatin and boiling water. Stir until completely dissolved; set aside.
In blender, puree chilled peaches with their syrup.
With blender running, slowly add gelatin mixture.
Pour into bowl; refrigerate until firm. (Will have a texture similar to mousse.)

title: marinated carrots
directions: Use a 1 quart can of cooked carrots or cook your raw carrots until tender.
Layer carrots, raw pepper and onion in a dish.
Set aside.
Heat tomato soup, vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard and margarine.
Mix well.
Pour this over your carrots and marinate overnight.
Heat and serve.

title: orange gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water then mix in cold water.
Add pecans, pineapple and bananas.
Chill until set.
Cook sugar, pineapple juice, eggs (slightly beaten) and cream cheese over low heat until thick.
Beat with electric mixer.
Let cool and spread on top of jello mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil a small unpeeled potato until soft.
Peel and mash potato in a mixing bowl.
Add powdered sugar a little at time and mix.
Keep doing this until a dough forms.
Roll out dough on waxed paper until about 1/4 inch thick.
Spread peanut butter on dough.
Roll into a log.
Cut into 1/4 inch thick slices.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill in refrigerator

title: chili pepper pork chops
directions: Get an oblong baking dish and marinate your pork chops for 3 hours, by covering with Worcestershire sauce.
Enough just to season, do not drench the pork chops in it.
Sprinkle with salt & pepper and garlic powder when ready to bake.
Cover with sliced mushrooms, chili peppers and chopped onions.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake until done in a 375 degree oven.
While pork chops are baking, make alfredo sauce.
Keep sauce simmering on low until [pork chops are done.
This will cook the flavor of the chili peppers into the sauce.
When serving the pork chops, cover with the sauce.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Leave cream cheese out of refrigerator for about 2 hours so that it will be soft.
Mix cream cheese, pineapple, 3/4 cup of pecans, green pepper, onion and seasoned salt in a large mixing bowl.
Form into 2 small balls or 1 large ball and roll in remaining pecans.

title: spiced tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags and add spices. Let stand 5 minutes. Then add juices, sugar, and 1 1/2 cup hot water. Serve hot.

title: cinnamon bears
directions: Roll a slice of bread in a ball.
Dip in melted butter.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and toast in moderate oven for about 10 minutes.
Fun for kids to make!

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into small balls, about the size of marbles.
Bake for about 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes about 80.
Cooked cheese balls can be frozen and heated later.
Wrap frozen cheese balls in foil and bake in 400° oven for 12 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on bag and drain.
Mix all ingredients together in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt ida's carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Very moist.

title: italian tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil and add garlic powder; brown 30 seconds.
Add tomato paste; brown 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add and stir to mix tomato juice, basil leaves, oregano and brown sugar.
Simmer, stirring to prevent scorching only.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Mix the onion, celery, green pepper and mayonnaise.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Saute mushrooms lightly.
Layer bread, mushrooms and onion mixture in baking dish.
Pour over all the milk/egg mixture.
Add 1 can mushroom soup just before baking. Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top and bake at 325° for 50 minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and continue baking for 10 minutes.

title: fruit flavor pops
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water. Pour into paper cups or pop molds. Freeze until almost firm, about 2 hours.
Insert wooden spoons or popsicle sticks.
Freeze until completely firm.
(I use 5 ounce Dixie paper cups.)

title: pear relish by celeste and marialice
directions: You will also need clean, hot jars and rings and lids.

title: old-fashioned brown sugar pie
directions: Melt butter and mix with flour, milk, eggs and brown sugar. Pour into pie shell and bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan and bake at 250° for about 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Beat together cream cheese and powdered sugar; spread on cookie crust. Strawberry filling, pineapple chunks and bananas should be layered on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with pecans and cherries.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine, salt and vanilla; chill. Insert cherry inside small ball of mixture.
Freeze balls, then dip balls into chocolate and wax mixture that has been melted in top of double boiler over very low heat.

title: chocolate-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet. Cream butter, sugar and pudding mix.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Batter will be very stiff.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Beat sugar, margarine and egg together.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Fold in zucchini, nuts and raisins.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush Oreos into small pieces in a large bowl.
Melt butter. Pour butter over Oreos and mix well.
Set aside.
In another large bowl, mix vanilla pudding as directed on box.
Fold into pudding a large container of Cool Whip.
Mix well until you have a smooth mixture.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Spread melted chocolate over the peanut butter mixture.
Put into refrigerator.
Cut into squares before the chocolate hardens too much.
Return to the fridge. Very good; tastes like Reese's Cups.

title: diced apple cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugars and beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and mix in alternately with the remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: 30 minute chicken noodle soup(tastes like it cooked for hours.)
directions: Heat oil in a large soup pot over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and brown.
Add in vegetables, thyme, salt, pepper. Reduce heat to medium and cover.
Sweat the vegetable for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add broth and bring to a boil.
Once boiling add in the noodles and cook 10 minutes, or until noodles are tender. Add in parsley and serve.
Yield 4-6 servings.

title: mrs. dwight d. eisenhower's uncooked fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water. Combine eggs, vanilla, cream and sugar.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Knead in nuts.
Pour onto greased platter and chill in the refrigerator before cutting.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Add sugar, flour, butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sour cream.
Fold in egg whites. Bake in a tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together thoroughly; shape into small balls.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Layer berries and wafers, 3 layers deep in large dish.
Beat powdered sugar, egg and canned milk into a syrup and pour over berries and wafers.
Whip the whipping cream and sweeten to taste and spread over top.

title: oven barbecue chicken(makes approximately 6 servings; baking time of 80 minutes)
directions: Early in the day, mix flour and salt.
Coat chicken.
Brown in skillet with 1/2 cup salad oil.
Drain and put chicken in 3-quart casserole.
Add onion to fat and saute.
Add celery, green pepper, catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and pepper.
Pour over chicken and chill.

title: rouladen(beef rolls)
directions: Pound beef slices with mallet until thin. Spread mustard on one side of each beef slice. Divide onions and bacon among the 8 beef slices. Roll up each slice, lengthwise, with filling in the center. Secure with string or toothpicks. Dredge beef rolls in flour and brown in hot oil in skillet. Add hot water with bouillon cubes and simmer in a 350° oven until fork-tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Remove rolls and thicken gravy with the cornstarch and add sour cream. Spoon gravy over rolls when served.

title: orange cranberry toddy (non-alcoholic drink)
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients to boiling point.
Taste and add more sugar if needed.
Garnish with orange slices and add cinnamon sticks for swizzlers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fettucini prima
directions: *May use Sprinkle Lite which has less fat.

title: quick chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken in freezer until firm enough to slice. Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Put about 1/2 cup of flour and 1 teaspoon poultry seasoning in a small paper bag.
Add the cut up chicken and shake until all pieces are coated with flour mixture.

title: jello fruit 'n juice squares
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for at least 2 minutes until dissolved. Mix orange juice and ice to make 1 1/4 cups. Stir into gelatin. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until slightly thickened. Remove 1 1/2 cups of the gelatin. Stir in fruit cocktail. Stir 1/2 tub Cool Whip into remaining gelatin with wire whisk until blended. Pour into

9-inch square dish. Refrigerate about 10 minutes until set, but not firm. Carefully spoon fruited gelatin over creamy layer in dish. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Cut into squares. Garnish with remaining whipped topping. Makes 9 servings.

title: pork roast
directions: You will also need 1 regular size oven cooking bag.

title: chocolate rum cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl. Beat 5 minutes. Pour into 10-inch tube or Bundt pan, well-greased. Do not flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool 30 minutes before removing from pan. Sift confectioners sugar over cake.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Add cream, extract and coconut.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 2 pie crusts and bake.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Store in jars. It will last all winter.

title: easy grasshopper pie
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine.
Press mixture onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Refrigerate.

title: dad's chitterlings
directions: Wash and pick chitterlings real good.
Pick most of the fat from them.
Cut into 5 to 6-inch lengths.
You better have 1/2 of a day to cook chitterlings.
Put chitterlings in pot with boiling water (to cover).
Slice lemons and onions and add to pot.
Boil until tender.
Remove from pot and drain.
Mix meal, flour, salt and pepper in double layered paper bag and put several pieces in bag and shake to coat.
Drop into hot oil and deep fry until golden brown and crispy.
Lift out and drain on paper towel. Serve hot.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Cut bacon into small cubes.
Wash and drain well.
Put in saucepan.
Fry out fat until bacon is crisp.
Add onion; cook until limp.
Add okra; continue cooking until okra is fork-tender. Add tomatoes; season to taste.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Blend together and beat 4 minutes.
Makes 2 large or 4 small loaves.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and let stand 2 days.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch glass dish.
Mix by hand sugar, flour, baking powder, dash of salt and milk.
Pour over butter and do not stir.
Have ready peaches and 3/4 cup sugar.
Spread peaches over batter.
Do not stir.
Serve warm.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: egg casserole
directions: Tear bread into pieces.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Cut cheese into chunks (medium size).
Layer in baking dish the bread, cheese and bacon.
Melt butter.
Add eggs, milk and mustard.
Stir and pour over bread.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Arrange apples in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients with fork; sprinkle over apples.
Bake until apples are tender and topping is golden brown (about 30 minutes).
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: natalie's party snack
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cut off top of bread and hollow out inside. Save bread for dipping. Put cheese mixture in bread loaf. Put top back on. Wrap loaf in foil twice (heavy foil best). Warm in oven at 400° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve hot.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar and vanilla in heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook to soft ball stage (243° on a candy thermometer). Stir frequently to prevent scorching.
Add pecan halves and stir to coat.
Turn onto buttered baking sheet and quickly separate pecans with two forks.
Makes about 1 1/4 pounds. Also good with peanuts.
May be packaged and frozen in airtight container.
Fill coffee mug full and give to friends for gifts!

title: salmon log
directions: Drain and flake salmon, removing cartilage.
Combine all other ingredients except parsley and pecans. Chill well.
Form into log. Roll in pecans and parsley which have been mixed together.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix with hands flour, powdered sugar and butter or margarine until it becomes soft dough.
Pat down in 13 x 9-inch baking dish that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Beat with mixer sugar, lemon juice and eggs.
Spread over first layer.
Put in oven and bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add onion and celery.
Separate broccoli and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: angel hair pasta with sea scallops
directions: Place bread crumbs on baking sheet.
Bake at 375 for 5 minutes or until golden brown; set aside.

title: apple crisp pudding
directions: Put fruit into buttered baking dish.
Pour water over fruit. Mix sugar, butter, flour and spices.
Spread over top of fruit. Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: golden punch
directions: Boil sugar and 2 quarts water together.
Add mint leaves; cook and strain.
Add tea, water and fruit juices to the other mixture. Just before serving, add 2 quarts ginger ale.
Top with orange and lemon slices.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salts, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonful into balls.
Place meatballs in ungreased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.

title: chinese-style cabbage
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Drop in vegetables; stir well.
Cover tightly.
Steam 5 minutes on medium heat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.
Good with Ham Loaf.

title: terry's mexican layered dip
directions: Brown meat in skillet, drain and rinse in a colander to reduce fat.
Return meat to skillet and add taco flavoring mix.
Follow instructions on package.
Set aside and let cool.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls into a lightly greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Firmly press perforations to seal. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over crust.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika and pepper.
In large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook, turning for 5 to 7 minutes until brown.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add mushrooms to skillet.
Cook, stirring often, for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, cream cheese and seasoning.
Mix well.
Then stir in Cheddar cheese and crab.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients except pretzels.
Coat pretzels with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir once.

title: chicken with vegetables
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Brown chicken in small amount of oil.
Mix soup and 1/2 can water; add to chicken.
Add chopped onion, peas, broccoli and Pasta Primavera.
Simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: frypan meal
directions: Slightly
brown the link sausage.
Over this, slice the potatoes.
Add a layer of sliced onions.
Sprinkle the remaining ingredients
on
top.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 to 60 minutes, or place in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: coconut, sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs one at a time, then beat well.
Add milk and flavoring; next, beat in flour and last, coconut and sour cream.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan.

title: cornish pasties
directions: Measure flour and salt into bowl.
Mix in shortening. Sprinkle in water 1 tablespoon at a time until flour is moistened and dough almost clears side of bowl (1 to 2 teaspoons water can be added if needed).
Roll out dough and cut into round circles.

title: lisa's pizza casserole
directions: Boil
noodles
and
drain.
Slice
meat and brown, then drain. Mix
in casserole dish.
Microwave:
4 minutes turning 1/2 way after 2 minutes.
Or bake in conventional oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck in a large frying pan, then add Prego spaghetti sauce, water, garlic powder and sugar.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Delicious!

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine until tender, as directed on box.
Rinse and cool.
Add tomatoes, cucumbers and onions.
Then add Italian dressing and salad seasoning.
Mix together and refrigerate for several hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix until well blended and slightly fluffy.
Combine flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and soda. Add to other mixture and blend well.
Add pumpkin and water, mixing until all ingredients are blended.
Grease and flour bottoms only of 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Drain.
Add tomato puree and spices. Bring to a slight boil.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Cook lasagne noodles according to package directions.
Grate cheese.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
(I use a Tupperware mix and fix bowl.)
Refrigerate in a tightly cover bowl.
Mix each day for 3 days.
On fourth day shape into 5 rolls, place on a broiler pan and bake at 175° for 8 hours.
Great for cheese trays, and as good if not better than store bought.

title: my mama's custard
directions: Sift sugar, flour and salt together.
Add to egg yolks.
Add milk gradually.
Cook over boiling water until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and butter.
Then cool.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs.
Mix.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: baked steak and gravy
directions: Roll steaks in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil.
Remove steaks from pan.
Brown 3 tablespoons flour in oil.
Add broth to make gravy.
Pour over steaks in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Bake the pie shells as directed. Divide the ham, cheese and onions between the 2 shells. In a bowl, whisk the eggs, cream, salt and pepper. Pour into the shells. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: potato salad(non-fattening--unless of course you eat too much!)
directions: Use a large mixing bowl and mix well with a strong spoon. Tastes best if refrigerated overnight.

title: cabbage chop suey
directions: Heat shortening in a large skillet over medium heat. Add vegetables, tossing lightly. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes. Add salt and pepper; cook, uncovered, 1 minute, stirring gently. Sprinkle with chow mein noodles, if desired. Serve immediately.

title: vegetable lo-mein
directions: Cut onion into 12 wedges, julienne the carrots and pepper. Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Heat a large wok, then add peanut oil.
Add onion and stir-fry until they are slightly tender and beginning to brown, about 2 minutes.
Add carrots, pepper, broccoli and garlic and continue to stir-fry about 2 minutes.
In a small bowl, stir together, oyster sauce and mirin.
Pour over vegetables immediately.
Add spaghetti or vermicelli and toss well to combine.
Remove from heat; splash with sesame oil.
Toss lightly.
Serve hot.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with cooking spray. Combine all ingredients, except chicken halves.
Dip chicken in mixture and place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sugar and dissolve.
Let jello cool while chopping all other ingredients in food processor. Mix chopped ingredients into jello.
Pour into mold or serving bowl.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook the chicken.
Reserve 2 cups broth and add the cream of chicken soup.
Let chicken cool, then take the meat off the bone. In a large bowl, combine the flour, buttermilk and black pepper. Melt the margarine.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan with broth, then spread with flour, buttermilk, black pepper and margarine.
Will make its own crust.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, cracker crumbs, celery, onions, cheese and salt; add eggs.
Stir in cream and butter.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: jellied peach creme
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill about 15 minutes; then add half and half and extract.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Garnish with chopped toasted almonds if desired.
Makes 2 1/4 cups or 4 servings.

title: dutch oven stroganoff
directions: Thin slice the steak into 1 x 1/2-inch pieces.
Stir the meat into a mix of 2 cups of flour, garlic powder, meat tenderizer, onion powder, curry powder and pepper.
After all the meat is evenly coated, sear by stir-frying in the vegetable oil.
Empty the cooked meat into large pan.
Add the sour cream, chopped Spanish onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Add water and remaining flour while stirring over medium-high heat, creating a smooth, light to medium brown gravy.
Cook egg noodles; pour gravy mix over and serve.

title: smoked rolled pork roast
directions: Prepare smoker per instructions.
Score pork roast.
Liberally moisten the entire roast with Worcestershire sauce.
Generously rub garlic powder over the roast with your hand to form a paste. Sprinkle pepper over entire roast to form a crust.
Smoke 4 hours. Serve immediately as main course or appetizer.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 cup water.
Saute celery and onion in butter.
Mix broccoli and water with rice, Cheez Whiz, soup and saute mixture.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: mock fruit jam
directions: Boil 15 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal with wax or use jars with lids.
I think raspberry is the best.

title: crunch corn dip
directions: Mix together and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Cook onions and pepper with some of the soup from the chicken. Add butter, Ro-Tel, peas, cheese, chicken and spaghetti.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no frosting cake
directions: Add milk to pudding mix; cook as per directions on box.
Let cool.
When cool, add dry cake mix to pudding.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with a vegetable spray.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over top of mixture.
Bake according to directions on cake mix.

title: milkless butterless eggless cake
directions: Bring sugar, water, shortening, raisins, nutmeg and cinnamon to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes; let cool.
Mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and nutmeats.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a square pan.
Mix remaining ingredients except fruit;
pour batter into pan.
Arrange fruit on top or pour batter
over fruit and butter/oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip; spread this over baked crust.
Put in refrigerator.
Mix jello and water.
Add strawberries.
Let stand 15 minutes, then pour over creamed mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: no-cook fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spread out into buttered pan and slice.

title: brownies
directions: Unwrap caramels and melt with 1/3 cup Pet milk.
Mix cake mix, melted butter and 1/3 cup Pet milk.
Divide batter in half and press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 4 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread melted caramels on top.
Next, top with chocolate chips and pecans.
Spread remaining cake mixture on top. After a few minutes, try to spread top layer of cake mixture better.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes more.
Cool!

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Spread 1 tablespoon Cheez Whiz on thawed tortilla and set aside.
Saute onion and pepper in butter. Add eggs and scramble.
Brown sausage, drain and mix with eggs. Put 3 tablespoons eggs on tortillas.
Fold and wrap individually in foil.
Heat for 5 minutes.
Can be frozen first and then heated.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Put into a large mixing bowl.
Add crabmeat, broken into bite-sized pieces.
Add chopped green pepper, thinly sliced celery and pickle relish.
Mix with enough mayonnaise to thoroughly moisten.
Mayonnaise will absorb as salad sets.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: spinach balls(appetizer)
directions: Mix ingredients by hand.
Form small (golf ball size) balls. Place on cookie sheet (non greased).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: holiday stuffing recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients in small, ovensafe bowl.
Wrap bowl in foil and bake for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini brownines
directions: Beat together eggs, oil and sugar.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and cocoa.
Mix all ingredients together and spread onto a cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef, onion and pepper. Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce, basil, oregano and garlic to ground beef after drained.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cottage cheese to sauce.
Cook noodles according to package.
Layer sauce, noodles and cheese.
Top with remaining cheese and cook for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix in a 9-inch baking pan the sugar, flour, cocoa and milk. Stir.
Combine sugars and 1/4 cup cocoa and sprinkle over batter. Pour water or coffee over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. This makes its own sauce.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Combine melted margarine, lemon juice and seasonings.
Dip fish fillets in this mixture and cover with bread crumbs.
Spread oil in baking dish and arrange fillets in 1 layer.
Spoon any remaining margarine mixture over fish and bake in 475° oven for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: banana split cake
directions: Place ingredients in 9 x 13-inch baking dish by layering pattern following: cherries, mini chocolate chips, Cool Whip, chopped nuts, pudding, bananas, pudding (mixed as directed) and crust.
Cool overnight before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients together, then add to peanut butter mixture.
Roll dough into balls the size of large walnuts.
Flatten with fork. Heat oven to 375° and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: spicy cheddar spread
directions: Grate cheese and stir in butter, pimento, onion, parsley and pepper.
Ready to serve.
Serve with toast or crackers.

title: hungarian cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage 15 minutes.
Cook bacon; lay aside.
Cook onion in bacon drippings.
Mix brown sugar, flour, water and vinegar; cook until thickened.
Drain cabbage, add to mix with bacon (crumbled).

title: zippy chicken strips
directions: Cut chicken into 3
x 1-inch strips and place in a shallow dish. Combine the next 3 ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover dish and marinate 30 minutes. Combine flour, pepper, salt and paprika.
Dredge chicken pieces in flour mixture.
Fry in hot oil (375°) until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chewy's
directions: Put all ingredients in mixer except 1/2 bag of toffee.
Put in 13 x 9-inch greased cake pan.
Sprinkle rest of toffee on top. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes only.
Cool before you cut.

title: zucchini, banana, pineapple bread
directions: Mix eggs, add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating until thick and foamy.
With spoon, stir in zucchini, bananas and pineapple.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in and mix well; add nuts.
Stir until mixed. Divide between 2 greased, floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes clean.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until moist.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple with juice, nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting and sprinkle with nuts.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix together well and form into a roll.
Roll out on foil. Sprinkle with chili powder and paprika.
Chill until firm.
Serve with Town House crackers or wheat crackers.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Slice round steak thinly and at an angle. You want 2 to 3-inch strips. Brown strips in Dutch oven or roaster. If you choose onions, brown them at the same time. Cover with 2 cans cream of mushroom soup. Cover roaster and roast in oven at 350° for 2 to 3 hours or whatever. If you choose whatever, check after 3 hours; add water if needed.

title: chicken afretada
directions: Wash the chicken very well.
Get a bigger pot; on medium heat, heat the cooking oil.
Put in the garlic; stir it with the oil, then put in the onion.
Keep stirring, then put in chopped tomatoes.
Keep stirring, then put in the chicken, mixed well. Cover to medium heat for 5 minutes, or until chicken turns a little bit brown, then put the paprika which has been mixed with 4 cups hot water.
Let it boil, then put in the potatoes mixed well. Cover; boil on medium heat for 30 minutes, or until potatoes and chicken are done, then turn off the stove.
Open the pot.
Put in the green pepper and red pepper, then cover for 3 minutes.
Food is ready to serve.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: corn patties
directions: Stir the corn into the well beaten egg yolks.
Add the salt, pepper and flour.
Beat the egg whites until they stand up in peaks.
Then fold them gently into the corn mixture.
Drop by tablespoon into a greased fry pan that is on medium heat.
Brown quickly on both sides.
Cook until they are golden brown.

title: homestyle turkey sausage
directions: Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Heat skillet over medium-high heat about 30 seconds.
Add turkey Italian sausage. Cover and cook 14 to 16 minutes or until lightly browned and no longer pink in center, turning occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients. Reduce heat to medium-low and cover; cook 30 to 35 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: kid's goulash
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Add soups and macaroni and cheese.
Heat through.
Serve.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Drain corn and beans.
Mix all ingredients together, except Ritz crackers and melted oleo.
Put into greased casserole dish; top with the Ritz crackers (crushed) with 1 stick melted oleo. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chops with fennel
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Rub garlic into each chop, then press fennel seeds on the surface of each chop.
Roll each chop lightly in flour.
In a lightly oiled skillet, brown chops on each side over medium heat.
Cover and cook until chops are tender.
Serve with brown rice or vermicelli.

title: country chicken & biscuits
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, combine chicken, bacon, vegetables and 1 cup cheese. Blend soup and the milk and pour over casserole. Bake covered at 400° for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, combine biscuit mix, milk and 1/2 can of onions. Mix thoroughly and drop by spoonfuls to form biscuits around the edge of the casserole. Bake uncovered for 15-20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown. Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake 2-3 minutes until onions are toasted. Makes 6-8 servings.

title: the best candied yams
directions: Put the yams in water and boil until they are cooked, then cool them and peel off the skin.
Place yams in buttered baking dish. Mix together the first five ingredients and spoon over the yams. Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, oil, eggs and vanilla until sugars are well blended (about 4 minutes).
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and stir into mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil together water, cloves and cinnamon.
Remove from heat. Add tea and steep for 5 minutes.
In a separate pan, heat orange juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Bring barely to boil.
Add to tea.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Make fluted edge of pie shell (1/2-inch on rim of pie plate). Stir pumpkin into eggs.
Blend salt, spices and sugar, then milk until well mixed.
Pour into pastry shell.

title: korean chocolate fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients (milk, butter and sugar); bring to a full boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add the chocolate morsels and Marshmallow Creme; mix fast and well to thoroughly melt the chocolate.
Add the vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a large greased pan.
(I cut the squares the next day; turn over squares and let stand several hours before storing.)

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, granulated sugar, beaten eggs, 1/4 c margarine, milk and vanilla together well and pour into a buttered shallow pan.

title: great fruit drink
directions: Pour orange juice in blender.
Add bananas and mix well.
Add strawberries and raspberries and mix.
Add honey and mix again. Add a little ice.
Mix again for a great refreshing drink.

title: butterfinger treats
directions: Spread peanut butter between cracker.
Melt chocolate and dip crackers.
You can either dip one side or both sides.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Combine graham crackers and butter. Press into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Beat eggs and softened cream cheese. Beat in sugar and vanilla. Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Serves 12.

title: pie crust for cobblers
directions: Cook fruit; add a little cornstarch to thicken.
Pour in a baking dish.
Let cool.
Mix remainder of ingredients.
Spoon over top of fruit.
You may have to use a little more milk to get the mixture soft enough to drop by spoonfuls over fruit or berries.

title: diet soda dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in lemon juice and cool soda.
Add the boiling soda and stir in fruit.
Chill until set as for jello. Entire amount makes 1 fruit serving.

title: cheese filled manicotti
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Cool. Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir together the cheeses, parsley, salt and pepper; spoon into cooled pasta tubes.
Spread thin layer of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange filled pasta in single layer over sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over pasta.
Cover with foil.
Bake 40 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake 15 minutes longer until hot and bubbly.

title: pecan candy roll
directions: Combine flavoring and cream; knead in sugar.
Shape in rolls, 1-inch in diameter, about 5-inches long.
Wrap in waxed paper and freeze.
Melt 1 pound Kraft caramels over boiling water.
Add 1 tablespoon water.
Remove from heat and dip rolls in melted caramel.
Roll in coarsely chopped nuts and press nuts in firmly.

title: no cholesterol fudgy brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup safflower oil. Add boiling water.

Stir until mixture thickens. Stir in sugar, Egg Beaters and remaining 1/3 cup oil. Stir until smooth. Add flour, vanilla and salt. Blend completely. Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan or two 8-inch square pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for a 13 x 9-inch pan or 30 to 32 minutes for 8-inch square pans.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a hole in the middle of the dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and bananas.
Oil loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue cups
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
In same saucepan, saute onion in margarine.
Remove from heat.
Add soup, pepper, egg, horseradish and mayonnaise; mix well.
Add broccoli, mix and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese, herb dressing mix and paprika.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 3 minutes more.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt over low heat the butter and peanut butter.
Add nuts, coconut and cracker crumbs.
Mix together.
Mix in powdered sugar and mix well.
Shape into balls and let cool.
Melt together butterscotch chips and Gulf Wax.
Roll candy in this mixture.
Set on waxed paper until cool.

title: delicious biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out and cut.
Put in small muffin pans, greased with Crisco.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Warm corn oil and oleo in a heavy pan.
Add onion, saute until onion is golden.
Add sliced carrots, turn heat on low and let the carrots saute.
Then add the cabbage, chopped in small pieces. Use only enough water to let them steam good.
Cook on low until carrots and cabbage are tender.
Let cook down low until the cabbage is very tender and begins to fry, just slightly.

title: lucille colbert's grapefruit salad
directions: Heat the grapefruit juice and sugar together to dissolve sugar.
Dissolve the gelatin in water or juice and add to sugar mixture.
Add grapefruit sections.
Divide in half.
Pour 1/2 in mold or in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Put in refrigerator or freezer to set.
Mix cream cheese with milk to spreading consistency.
Add nuts and either onion or garlic salt.
When mixture is set, spread over it.
Pour remaining 1/2 of mixture over this.
Refrigerate until firmly set.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Combine dry ingredients in saucepan, blend in water.
Bring to a boil over heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for two (2) minutes.
Add one (1) quart of milk and heat through (do not boil).
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat with rotary beater until foamy.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugars, salt, margarine and vanilla; mix well. Add eggs.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cherry squares
directions: Beat sugar, butter, margarine and eggs until light and fluffy. Add lemon juice, then flour.
Mix well and pour batter on ungreased cookie sheet and spread.
Put 2 or 3 cherries on each square.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into balls.
(Do not brown.)
Simmer meat balls in a sauce of 1 quart of ginger ale and 32 ounces of ketchup.
Do not stir until they have cooked for 20 minutes.
They do not fall apart.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: green chile
directions: Simmer	chicken filets in stock until done.
Remove and dice. Saute
onion
and
garlic in olive oil; add chicken and green chilies
for
a
couple minutes.
Add cilantro to saute mix.
Add saute mix and remaining ingredients to stock. Simmer to desired consistency and flavor.

title: beef stew with wine
directions: Brown garlic in margarine; take out and discard.
Brown onions, remove and put in casserole.
Brown carrots; put in casserole. Dust meat in flour, pepper and salt.
Brown meat.
Put everything back in skillet and add wine, consomme and bay leaf.
Mix ingredients and return to casserole.
Cover and simmer in a 350° oven about 4 hours.
Stir occasionally to keep from getting too brown on top.
Juice should be thickening perfectly but cautiously add more liquid if it appears to be drying out.

title: velvet almond cake
directions: Chop almonds and toast for 3 to 5 minutes in a 350° oven. Lightly grease and flour a tube cake pan.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in one gallon pitcher.

title: applesauce yogurt delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Measure 3/4 cup gelatin into small bowl; add applesauce and cinnamon.
Pour into individual dessert dishes.
Chill until set, but not firm.
Chill remaining gelatin until slightly thickened.
Blend in yogurt.
Spoon over set gelatin in dessert dishes.
Chill until set, about 2 hours. Garnish with additional yogurt, apple slices and mint leaves, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, combine juice, ketchup, honey, vinegar, mustard and salt.
Pour over the chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake about 30 minutes longer until meat is tender. Remove chops to platter and keep warm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add soups, beans and Ro-Tel.
Mix well.
Spread Doritos in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour heated mixture over chips.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: guacamole supreme
directions: Peel and seed avocados.
Add all other ingredients.
Mash until almost smooth.
Cover well and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind Oreos in blender or food processor.
Mix everything else in a large bowl.
Alternate layers of Oreos and mixture in a punch bowl and chill.

title: carrot-raisin nut salad
directions: Mix carrots, walnuts, raisins, sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and orange juice very well.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: peanut butter tandy take cake
directions: Bring milk and butter to a boil.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour large cookie sheet with sides. Spread batter on sheet.
Bake approximately 20 to 25 minutes. (Check frequently and remove when golden.)
Spread peanut butter over hot cake.
Cool.
Melt Hershey bars.
Spread over cool cake. This tastes just like the Tasty Kake Tandy Cakes you buy, but makes tons.
Great for a picnic or covered dish!

title: low cholesterol chicken
directions: Line baking dish with foil.
Place chicken, meat side down. Mix all ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover with foil. Bake 1 hour at 450°.

title: mexico chiquito punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir to dissolve sugar. Serve over ice and garnish with orange slices.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: punch
directions: Combine orange juice, pineapple juice and chill.
Just before serving, add chilled ginger ale.
Use an ice cream scoop to spoon balls of sherbet into punch.
Serves 35.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put milk in double boiler.
Melt marshmallows and Hershey bar (I only use 3/4 of the bar).
Let cool at room temperature.
Fold in whipping cream.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill 6 hours.

title: caramel apple cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the pie filling and chopped apple; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, brown sugar and flour.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Add eggs and yolk, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in cinnamon, extract and nutmeg.
Stir in whipping cream.
Pour half of the cream cheese mixture over the crust.
Spoon on 1 cup of the apple mixture.
Pour the remaining cream cheese mixture over the apple; top with remaining apple mixture.
Without disturbing the crust, swirl the blade of a knife throughout the filling to distribute the fruit evenly.

title: spinach soup
directions: Cook frozen chopped spinach in unsalted water according to directions and drain.
Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add onion and saute until transparent (5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Stirring constantly, gradually add milk, then add spinach.
Cook over medium-high heat (about 15 minutes).
Stir often to prevent scorching.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir well.
Serves several.
Can add 1/2 cup chopped celery.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well. Form into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 15
to 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onions.
Drain and mash down.
Add butter; stir until melted.
Place in casserole dish and add mushroom soup and grated cheese.
Mix.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 325° for 20 or 30 minutes.

title: new england bean pot casserole
directions: Core and chop apple.
Fry and crumble bacon.
Mix all ingredients together and turn into casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli-shrimp fettuccine
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Cook broccoli as directed, drain and set aside.
Cook fettuccine noodles as directed and set aside.

title: avocado soup
directions: Puree avocados, lemon juice and stock in blender.
Combine with cream of milk.
Add salt and pepper.
Barely heat through, stirring gently.
Just before serving, add green onions for garnishing.
Can be served hot or cold.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Homemade sauce:
Melt butter.
Add cream and nutmeg.
Boil rapidly until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese; serve warm.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugars and syrup to a boil. Add peanut butter, cornflakes and nuts. Press into a 9-inch pan. Melt chocolate and spread over top.

title: hot ham buns
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spread mixture on buns and wrap sandwiches in foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. These may be frozen and heated when needed.
Makes 4 or 6.

title: brenda's dressing
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a 10 x 10-inch baking dish or pan.
Put oleo pats on top of dressing mixture.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine boiling water, oats, brown sugar, butter and salt. Cool to warm. Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water. Add to batter. Add whole-wheat flour and white flour, enough to make smooth elastic dough (5 cups). Let rise until double in bulk. Punch down. Let rise again. Shape in small loaves and put in greased pans. Let rise again. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ding-a-ling candy
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler.
Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Chill.

title: apricot fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit and mix in a large bowl. Add pie filling and chill. Slice bananas into salad just before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chipped ham
directions: Brown onion in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mustard, water, brown sugar, lemon juice, catsup and cayenne pepper.
Add ham and simmer for 30 minutes.
Put hot ham mixture on a hamburger bun.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and heat it to boiling.
Stir until Jell-O is completely dissolved.
Add buttermilk; refrigerate until mixture begins to congeal.
Add nuts and fold in whipped topping. Chill at least 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: oven meatballs(porcupines)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine beef, rice, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and onion.
Shape into meatballs.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Mix soup and water; pour over meatballs.
Cover tightly; bake for 1 hour, or until done.
Serve with more rice and green salad.

title: pink jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple in pan (do not boil).
Use all of the juice. Dissolve Jell-O into warm pineapple; let it cool.
After it's cool, add buttermilk (I beat it with a mixer to make it smooth). Add Cool Whip and pecans.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit and put in baking dish. Melt butter and sugar. Add curry powder and 1/2 of apricot or pineapple juice. Pour over fruit and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar and spices to a boil.
Add the peach halves and cook until tender.
Refrigerate in syrup until ready to use.
Delicious with ham!

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Layer potatoes, onion, meat, beans, salt and pepper in casserole dish, until nearly full.
Pour tomato sauce over all. Cover and bake 1 hour in slow oven (250° to 300°).
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer.
Serve piping hot as one dish meal with a salad.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Mix with fork until mixture is like corn meal.
Spread half the mixture in pastry shell.
Set remaining mixture aside.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine pineapple, water and soy sauce in large frypan.
Add spices and bring to boil.
Add chicken.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Great served with rice.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello in 2 cups boiling water and set aside in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve marshmallows in 1 1/3 cups boiling water.
Pour into jello and cool.
Add pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Put in refrigerator and jell.

title: jam and cheese loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in biscuits mix, egg and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Mix well.
Turn onto surface dusted with additional biscuit mix.
Knead gently for 20 strokes. Place dough into center of greased 15 1/2 x 12-inch baking sheet. Roll to 14 x 9-inches.

title: beatrice griffin's leather britches
directions: You will also need a darning needle, coarse thread and cloth bags or old pillowcase.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter, baking powder and vanilla.
Add flour and mix.
Put in greased cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350°.

title: prize winning strawberry cake
directions: Let strawberries thaw and then mash. Mix jello with cake mix and add strawberries and juice from berries. Add eggs and oil. Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: south of the border stew
directions: Brown hamburger, add onion and saute for a few minutes.
When doubled (recipe) only use juice from 1 can of olives.
Serve with cornbread or rolls.

title: joann's cream of spinach soup
directions: Melt butter and oil in large saucepan; add onion and saute until transparent, about 5 minutes.
Press defrosted spinach in strainer.
Reserve liquid.
Add spinach to onion.
Mix well. Sprinkle with flour.
Stir.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Blend in broth and reserved spinach liquid.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in half and half, pepper and nutmeg and simmer 5 more minutes.
Add bacon and serve.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil and chop chicken.
Layer bottom with Doritos, rice, cheese, chicken, soups, cheese and top with Doritos (crushed). Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix and keep in jar to use.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons per cup of water.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix Jiffy, egg and milk.
Bake, cool and crumble.
Mix in large bowl, tomatoes, onion, pepper, celery and sweet pickles. Add bacon.

title: microwave fudge(peanut butter or chocolate)
directions: In microwave bowl, combine sugar, butter and canned milk.
Put in microwave 4 minutes on High.
Stir, then 4 minutes again on High.
Stir, then 3 minutes on High. Take out of microwave.
Add Marshmallow Creme.
Stir, then add peanut butter or chocolate chips.
Stir until smooth and pour into an 8 x 10-inch greased dish.
Let set.
Cut into squares.

title: pie filling cookie bar
directions: Beat all of the ingredients (except pie filling) for 3 minutes.
Spread onto a 10 x 14-inch greased and floured pan. Pour a can of pie filling over the top of this.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Let stand overnight.
Bake next morning.
Drop in small spoonfuls with pieces of pecan on each one.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine beans and chopped vegetables in bowl.
Mix well.
Add cheese and corn chips.
Pour dressing over salad; mix lightly.

title: dilly dip
directions: Chill and serve with chips or especially good with raw vegetables.
(The brand name for the dill weed and Beau Monde seasoning is Spice Islands.)

title: the "olympic" outstanding oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together, butter and sugar until light and fluffy; blend in egg and vanilla.
Add combined oats, flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet about 3 inches apart. Press 2 to 3 additional candies into each cookie, if desired.

title: stuffed chicken
directions: Put 1 slice of ham and tomato on each cutlet, rolling each one.
Wrap each in Saran Wrap tightly and steam for 25 minutes in steamer.

title: no. 2 sausage quiche
directions: Place pie crust in pan and crease edges.
Spread butter over pie crust.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Whip together the eggs, sausage, seasonings and cheese.
Place mixture in pie crust and sprinkle some cheese over top.
Bake 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 325° and bake 35 minutes.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, cream of tartar, and sugar into bowl.
Cut in shortening till mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well; add milk all at once.
Stir quickly with fork just till dough follows fork around bowl.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
(Dough should be soft.)
Knead lightly 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll or pat dough 1/2-inch thick.
Dip cutter in flour; cut dough straight down--no twisting.
Baking on ungreased baking sheet in 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 16 medium biscuits.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juices from fruit.
Add juices to lemon pudding.
Make as thick as you want.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Add oranges last.

title: wonderful custard
directions: Heat the milk, sweetening and salt.
Stir the hot milk slowly into the lightly beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Pour the mixture into custard cups.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) in pan of water (1-inch).
Bake until the custards are set or when the blade of a knife comes out clean.
Remove from hot water immediately.
Serve hot or cold.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet. Add potatoes and spices. Brown potatoes on both sides. Scatter onion over all and cook with lid on until tender (turn gently once or twice).

Spread eggs over all and cover with grated cheese. Cook on very low temperature with lid on until eggs are set, approximately 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with ketchup and horseradish, if desired. Serves 4.

title: richard's mexican casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onion until brown.
Add green pepper, cream of mushroom soup, Pet milk and tomatoes.
Mix well and let simmer for 1 hour.
(Add a little water if sauce gets too thick.) Line a baking dish with tortillas; cover with meat sauce and repeat layers.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Fold Cool Whip and dry Jell-O together.
Add marshmallows and strawberries and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry sparkle cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on back of package and cool.
Dissolve jello in water and add frozen block of strawberries, stirring to break up.
Cut 1 inch layer from top of cake.
Cut a tunnel into cake.
Gently remove sections of cake from the middle, tear into small pieces.
Fold pieces into strawberry mixture and spoon into cake.
Place cake layer on top.
Spread whipped cream on cake. Refrigerate until serving time or at least 1 hour.

title: wham dandy
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Saute onion and garlic in butter until clear.
Add the browned Ham Style Entree, cottage cheese, mushroom soup, milk and cooked noodles.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix the shortening, sugar, baking powder, nuts, milk, flour, eggs, lemon rind and lemon extract.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 90 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes, then glaze.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, except the corn flakes.
The crushed corn flakes are mixed with melted butter and spread over the whole mixture.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan for 1/2 hour.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine eggs and milk; set aside.
In a bowl, combine flour, corn meal, salt and pepper.
Slice tomatoes into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Dip them into the egg mixture, then dredge in corn meal mixture until well coated.
Fry in bacon drippings until golden brown, turning once.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Saute ground beef and onion in margarine. Add water, tomatoes, celery, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper, bay leaf and Worcestershire sauce.

title: apricot squares
directions: Combine apricots and water; steam until tender. Add 3/4 cup granulated sugar. Cook until thick and tender. Cool. Sift flour, salt and soda together. Cream butter or margarine, gradually adding 1 cup granulated sugar; beat well. Blend in dry ingredients. Stir in coconut and pecans. Press 3 cups of this crumbly mixture in bottom and halfway up sides of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until it looks golden in color. Spread apricot mixture over crust evenly. Sprinkle remaining crumbly mixture on top of apricots. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Cool. Cut into squares. Makes about 1 dozen pieces.

title: deluxe shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni, rinse and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Dump in macaroni.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add the rest. Chill in refrigerator 1 hour (optional).

title: sailboat salads
directions: You will need 4 cocktail toothpicks.

title: corn flake chocolate chips
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt onto wax paper.
Beat butter and sugar and brown sugar in large bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Beat in water, egg and vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Gently stir in chocolate morsels and corn flakes.
Drop mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls 1 inch apart onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake in oven for 5 minutes or until cookies are set and golden brown.
Cool on cookie sheets several minutes.
Transfer to wire rack; cool completely.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: chicken in a dark and mysterious sauce(from chocolate lovers dinner)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F.

title: taco grande dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: one hour yeast rolls(no kneading)
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add buttermilk, shortening and sugar.
Mix well.
Add flour a little at a time, stirring with a spoon.
Beat
until smooth.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Shape as desired, dusting with flour.
Place in greased pan.
Let rise 30 minutes in warm place.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: helen's chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine onion, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and nuts; mix well.
Form into ball.
Roll in chipped beef. Chill; serve with assorted crackers.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix meal, oil, eggs and corn well; fold in sour cream.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: mardi gras king cake
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt, and shortening in saucepan.
Scald, then cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl, then add eggs, lemon rind, nutmeg, milk mixture and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour, a cup at a time. Knead on floured board until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turn, then cover with a damp cloth.
Let rise in warm place about 2 hours.

title: pecan cake
directions: Mix raisins and pecans together and sprinkle with a little flour.
Set aside.
Mix thoroughly all dry ingredients.
Cream butter; add sugar and cream well.
Beat eggs well with a fork and add slowly to butter-sugar mixture; mix well.
Add molasses and apple juice.
Fold in dry ingredients; add nuts and raisins. Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
(I make this in two angel food cake pans and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.)
When cool, wrap in cloth soaked in apple juice for at least two weeks before serving.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Beat egg until very fluffy.
Add salad oil and keep beating until incorporated and thickened.
Then add rest of ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: cajun "hot dog" sauce
directions: Place hamburger in large pan of cold, salted water.
Bring to a boil, breaking up meat with spoon until fine consistency.
Drain meat.
Mix all ingredients with meat.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring often.
(Add a little water if too thick).
If a stronger flavor is desired, add more chili powder.
Serve over hot dog and bun. (Great to eat while watching the Saints!!!)

title: pirozhki
directions: In large bowl, put flour.
Cut in butter and shortening .
Cut until fat is about pea sized.
Add spoonful at a time the vinegar mixed with ice water.
Gather dough into a ball.
Divide into 2 balls.
Refrigerate.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Make Jell-O according to package directions.
Chill until soft set.
Stir in walnuts and apple that has been cored, then diced. (Retain or remove apple peel according to your preference.)
Chill until stiff.
Serves six.

title: extra rich brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mixer may be used.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool, cut, serve and enjoy.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in lemonade.
Add cold water and cranberry juice.
Pour in punch bowl.
Add chilled ginger ale, ice or ice mold.

title: pineapple parte
directions: Roll wafers to fine crumbs.
Divide and put half in shallow 8 x 10-inch pan (save the other half for top).
Cream the butter and sugar together well.
Add eggs, one at a time; cream well after each.
Pour this over crumbs.
Drain juice from pineapple; spread pineapple over batter, then add whipped cream.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs and pat lightly into cream.
Store in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Cut and serve.

title: lo-cal blueberry cream pie
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package; cool slightly.
Pour into baked shell.
Cover with waxed paper; chill until set.
Top with Blueberry Topping; top with whipped topping.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes; reserve 1/2 stick oleo (melted) and corn flakes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Mix butter and corn flakes; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy chicken salad
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed.
Mix in next 6 ingredients. Salt to taste and serve hot or cold.

title: goulash
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add meat.
Brown and drain.
Add tomato sauce.
Slice cheese into mixture and let melt.
Add cooked noodles.
Add sour cream, and, of course, use other seasoning to your liking.
Simmer.

title: cavatini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta and drain.
Saute onion, green peppers and mushrooms in oil.
Mix onion mixture with pasta, pepperoni and sauce.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan or 4-quart casserole dish.
Place cheese on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Work shortening, sugar (in a separate bowl) and cream.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with banana and nuts. Pour into greased loaf pan (9 x 5-inch).
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Double recipe to make 3.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in an airtight container. Fill mug 1/4 full of mix and add hot water to serve.

title: savory rice
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine rice, soups and mushrooms. Cut up butter and place on top. Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Stir, then bake 15 minutes more. Bake at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, then add eggs, melted margarine, sugar and salt. Knead in flour. Put in covered bowl in refrigerator overnight. Dough will double in size.
Pinch rolls out each day as needed. Dough will stay good in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: strawberry graham cracker dessert
directions: Roll graham crackers to fine crumbs.
Add butter and sugar. Mix well and pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan, reserving 3/4 cup for top. Melt marshmallows with milk in double boiler.
Cool.
Add unsweetened cream which has been whipped.
Place layer of marshmallow mix in pan then strawberries and nuts and add remaining marshmallow mixture.
Make sure strawberries are covered.
Top with reserved graham cracker crumbs.
Chill in refrigerator overnight. Makes 12 servings.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mash bananas and mix with milk, egg whites and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and mix.
Pour into muffin tins lined with paper cups.
Bake at 425° for 17 minutes. Store in plastic bag in refrigerator.
Makes 12.

title: lemon wafers
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg, lemon rind and lemon juice, beating well. Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing just until blended.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful, about 2 inches apart, on cookie sheets coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately and cool on wire rack.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen (about 49 calories each).

title: custard without eggs(low cholesterol)
directions: Combine powdered milk, sugar, cornstarch and water.
Mix well. Bring water to a boil; add to the mixture.
Cook in double boiler over low heat until thick.
Add margarine, vanilla and food color.

title: best cornbread you'll ever eat
directions: Put oil (or bacon fat) in skillet to preheat.
Place heavy iron skillet in 400° oven to preheat.
Combine cornmeal and milks. Stir in sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Gently stir in flour and soda (mix together before adding to wet) until moist.
Stir in crumbled bacon, if desired.
Bake 20 minutes at 400° or until golden brown.

title: unfried chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Coat a baking sheet with 3 sprays of vegetable oil.
Put the chicken in a large bowl with the ice water.
Put the yogurt into a medium bowl.
Set both aside.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt margarine; mix in rest of ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hobo stew
directions: Brown hamburger. Saut onion, celery and peppers. Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish; add water to desired consistency (start with a little more water or it will become really thick). Bake, with lid on, at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 45 minutes or until potatoes are done. Stir occasionally while cooking. Serve with dinner rolls.

title: crunchy apple crisp
directions: Place apple pie filling in shallow 1-quart baking dish.
In a bowl, combine flour, oats, brown sugar, salt and spices.
Add butter; mix well.
Spread topping evenly over pie filling.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with or without ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: layered meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in bowl; set aside.
Microwave margarine in glass baking dish on High until melted.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Microwave for 3 minutes.
Add thyme, cumin, sour cream and bread crumbs.
Mix well.

title: easy brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the pan and mix together.
These are rich and good.

title: pound cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Blend flour into butter mixture.
Add flavoring.
Refrigerate dough until thoroughly chilled.
Form into small balls about the size of a quarter and press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Using thumb, press indentation in top of each cookie and fill with small amount of strawberry jam.
If you prefer, press a pecan half on top of cookie.
Bake 12 minutes at 300° or until lightly browned.
Cool several minutes, then slide cookies off pan using a spatula.
Keep stored in an airtight container.
Yield:
6 to 7 dozen.

title: braunschweiger party spread
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Serve immediately or refrigerate spread approximately 1 hour and shape into ball and cover with nuts.
Serve with crackers, chips or fresh vegetables.

title: chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons of margarine (reserve 1 tablespoon) until smooth.
Add next
4 ingredients; mix well.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center of chicken mixture; twist slightly and seal edges.
Brush tops with reserved margarine; dip in crumbs.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spaghetti viennese
directions: Saute garlic in butter until soft.
Add half of cream, most of the feta cheese and some Parmesan cheese.
Stir.

title: yummy peach salad
directions: Heat
jello and pineapple in saucepan until it comes to a hard boil.
Remove and let cool.
Stir in 2 cups buttermilk and 1 large Cool Whip.
Mix all together and chill.

title: dogs in blankets
directions: You will need some green sticks.

title: pickle beets
directions: Cook beets.
Leave 2 inches of top stems while cooking.
When beets are clean from all dirt, boil about 20 minutes to 1 hour, according to size, until tender.
Drain off and use cold water to cool enough to peel.
When peeled, put in clean pot.
Add vinegar, sugar and spices.
If vinegar is too strong, add a little water. Heat to simmer.
Pack in hot jars; seal.
Should make 6 pints.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Put cheese in just before serving.

title: oklahoma dip
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients together and drain. Add two 10-ounce cans Ro-Tel tomatoes and 2 pounds Velveeta cheese.
Cook slowly until cheese melts. Serve warm with Fritos or Doritos.

title: frozen strawberry preserves
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar and let stand 20 or 30 minutes.
Mix Sure-Jell with water.
Boil for 1 minute.
Pour over strawberries and mix well.
Put in flat pan and let stand overnight.
(Stir occasionally.)
Put in jars, paraffin and put in freezer.
If you have some leftover from the meal just re-freeze.

title: peanut butter chocolate kisses
directions: Beat peanut butter and butter.
Add sugar and beat well.
Mix in egg and vanilla.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Cover bowl and chill dough for 1 hour.
Shape dough into small balls (1 x 3-inch). Bake 5 minutes in a 350° oven.
Take out of oven and press kiss into top of cookie.
Return to oven for 3 minutes.
Cool.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in order given in 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Chill for several hours.

title: apricot mold
directions: Heat 2 of the cups of apricot nectar.
Blend all ingredients in blender and pour into mold.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Thaw pie shells while mixing ingredients.
Prepare stuffing. Add drained vegetables, cream of chicken soup and stuffing into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: veg-a-bobs
directions: Cut bell pepper, onion and mushrooms in half or fourths, depending on size.
Place all veggies on sticks in random, about 2 each of every veggie.
Place in foil pan.
Veggie sticks can be stacked on top of each other.
Melt butter.
Pour over veggies, making sure all have been basted.
Along with butter in bottom of pan, pour some water for steaming.
Cover with foil, leaving ends open a little.
Place on grill over medium heat until tender.
You can also place 2 or 3 shrimp on each stick if desired, uncooked and peeled.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Place chicken in greased casserole pan.
Salt and pepper.
Cover with rice. Sprinkle remaining ingredients over rice.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in order.
