Mix together mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread this on top of layered vegetables.
Spread shredded Cheddar cheese and bacon bits on top.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Heat apple juice concentrate; thicken with cornstarch.
Stir in butter and cinnamon.
Pour over apples in large bowl; stir carefully.
Sprinkle with salt.
Pour into crust.
Cover with top crust, sealing edge.
Brush top with milk and sprinkle with additional cinnamon.
Cut steam vents.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp cajun
directions: Make in electric frypan at 300°.
Melt butter, saute onion, pepper and celery.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Add tomatoes and cover; let simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir.
Add cooked shrimp, cheese tortelles, ham and frozen peas.
Let simmer 15 minutes at 220°.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Place butter in a large mixing bowl.
Place dates on top and pour both sugars over.
Pour boiling water over ingredients in the boil. Let sit for 7 minutes; stir well.
When mixture is cool, add the egg and mix well.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to date mixture, beating for 30 seconds.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sauce for meatloaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes. Baste your favorite meatloaf before cooking.

title: elbow salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions.
Mix all remaining ingredients in blender.
Pour over rotini and toss. Serve chilled.

title: dilled chicken fricassee(a one pot dinner)
directions: Mix flour, salt, paprika.
Coat chicken (set aside the rest of flour mixture).
Fry chicken, skin side down (can use skinless chicken) 3 minutes or until browned.
Turn meat, add rest of flour mixture.
Gradually stir in chicken broth.
Then add only 2 Tbsp. of the dill.
Bring to a boil, add potatoes, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add green beans, cover and simmer 10 more minutes until chicken and potatoes are tender and beans are crisp and tender.
Stir in lemon juice and remaining dill.
Serve.

title: caramel walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and egg.
Cut in 1/2 cup margarine until crumbly.
Stir in walnuts. Reserving 2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Blend with hand mixer the first 3 ingredients in small bowl. Then stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish and freeze.
Remove 10 minutes or so before serving to soften enough to cut into squares.
Serve on leaf lettuce.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine the chicken, celery, walnuts, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Toss the salad gently to mix.
Add mayonnaise and mix lightly.
Refrigerate it until well chilled.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook and drain noodles.
In a 2 quart greased baking dish, pour a layer of ingredient mixture, then a layer of noodles.
Continue alternating layers.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Garnish with minced parsley.

title: zippy zucchini soup
directions: Cut ends off zucchini and slice into 1-inch pieces.
Place in a 6-quart saucepan.
Add salt, onion powder, garlic powder, white pepper, chicken broth and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over moderate heat until tender, about 10 minutes.

title: sandbakkles
directions: Combine ingredients in order. Shape into sandbakkle tins. Bake in 375° oven until light brown.
For easy handling put tins on cookie sheets.
Cool before removing from tins.

title: favorite buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar, soda and salt. Combine egg, milk and salad oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Bake on hot griddle.
Makes about 12 dollar size or eight (4-inch) pancakes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix together in blender.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch pie pan. Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon of butter or margarine and saute mushrooms for approximately 5 minutes.
Set mushrooms aside.
In large saucepan, melt 1 tablespoon of butter and saute carrots, celery and onion for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining butter to saucepan and melt.
Stir in flour.
Cook over medium heat for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chicken and beef broth, a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook over medium heat.
Add milk into mixture, a little at a time, stirring after each addition.
Add mushrooms to soup and slowly stir in cream.
Add dash of white pepper.
(If soup is thicker than desired, add more milk.)

title: stuffed turkey breasts
directions: Remove fillets from breast halves.
Starting with thinner edge, cut each breast in half lengthwise horizontally, almost all the way through.
Open and pound to 1/4-inch.
Combine 3 tablespoons soy sauce, sherry and sugar in a large shallow dish. Add turkey, skin side down; marinate 30 minutes.
Combine bread, celery, almonds and onions.
Blend butter with remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce; toss with bread mixture until moist and crumbly.
Remove turkey; reserve marinade.
Spread half of the stuffing mixture on half of each breast half, leaving a narrow border along outside edges; pack stuffing down slightly.
Close breasts and secure with toothpicks; brush with reserved marinade. Place on rack in baking pan.
Roast at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until tender, brushing with reserved marinade every 30 minutes.
Remove to serving platter; let stand 15 minutes.
Remove toothpicks and cut crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.

title: crisp zucchini pancakes
directions: Place zucchini in colander after shredding.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt. Set aside for 30 minutes.
Squeeze as much liquid as possible from zucchini with your hands.
Reserve.

title: peanut buster parfait
directions: Crush cookies and mix with melted margarine.
Press 3/4 of mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread soft ice cream over crumbs and freeze.

title: fried mackerel in sauce
directions: For mackerel (in separate bowl), mix together 1/4 cup salt and fresh chopped pepper.
Rub on fish; let set overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and flour mixture; stir only until moistened.
Pour into 2 greased and sugared 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Yield:
2 large loaves.

title: cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries (saving juice).
Mix sugar and flour in a saucepan and add cherry juice, coloring and extract.
Blend in carefully.
Stir in cherries.
Let stand while making crusts. Bake 5 minutes at 450°; reduce heat to 375° and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole(yields 12 servings)
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Spoon cheese sauce on top or sprinkle on grated cheese.
Layer rice and broccoli mixture with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Slivered almonds may be added to casserole for a special flavor.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: peaches and cream cheese cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes. Pour into 10-inch pie pan.
Place one can sliced peaches (drained) over batter.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and juice in mixer and pour over peaches to within 1-inch of edge of batter.

title: corn pudding
directions: Empty cans of corn into baking dish. Mix eggs, sugar, flour and milk well. Add mixture to corn and mix thoroughly. Salt and pepper to taste. Dot with butter. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix meatballs; form in balls and roll in uncooked rice.
Cover with tomato juice and cook at 325° for 2 hours or more.
Add more tomato juice during cooking.

title: chinese pork salad
directions: In large nonstick skillet, stir-fry pork over medium-high heat, about 4 to 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, toss pork with remaining ingredients.
Serves 4.

title: ice cream fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips, marshmallows and evaporated milk together in double boiler on low heat.
Add walnuts; let cool. Layer vanilla ice cream on crust, then fudge sauce, then ice cream and more fudge sauce until pan is fill.
Freeze.

title: weight watchers strawberries and wine
directions: In bowl, combine strawberries, wine and sweetener.
Stir and set aside for 30 minutes.
Stir thoroughly.
In blender, place 1/2 ice and 1/2 strawberry mix; process until smooth.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Pour into bowl and cover.
Place in freezer for 3 hours or until slushy.
Scoop into glasses and top with whipped topping.

title: oven fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine corn meal, salt and pepper; set aside.
Combine egg and water; beat well.
Drip tomatoes in egg mixture; dredge in corn meal mixture.
Lightly coat a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
Place tomatoes in a single layer in pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown, turning once. Makes 6 servings.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Place roast in deep pan.
Cover half way up with water. Cover with foil.	Cook in 325° oven until meat falls off bone, about 3 hours.
Cool.
Remove fat and bone.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: crunch bars
directions: Mix well.
Press firmly into a greased 7 1/2 x 11-inch pan. Bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spinach cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw and drain spinach completely. Mix all ingredients (except pie crust) in large bowl.
Fill pie crust shell and bake 40 minutes or until a knife slits the center and comes out clean.
Let sit a few minutes before slicing.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Bring to fast rolling boil the tomatoes, water, salt, pepper, oleo and sugar. Combine all dry ingredients; cut in Crisco. Add just enough water to make stiff dough. Roll out thin; cut in 2-inch squares. Roll each square in flour. (This keeps the dumplings from sticking together.) Drop squares individually into boiling tomatoes. Cover; turn to low and cook 15 minutes. Stir occasionally to keep from sticking. They are better made ahead of time and allowed to season. Reheat by placing them in a slow oven.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Combine melted chocolate, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at
a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to chocolate mixture, mixing well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Roll each in powdered sugar and roll again between palms of hands.
Place 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes (center will be somewhat soft).
Remove from rack to cool.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: prickly meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomato soup and water.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls about 1 inch in diameter and put in a 1-quart casserole.
Combine soup and water and pour over the meatballs.
Cover and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: seven layer taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together, then layer as listed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve chilled.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix Ro-Tel, enchilada sauce, chili and browned ground beef. Layer in casserole dish tortilla chips, mixture, tortilla chips, mixture and top with cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend condensed milk, egg yolks, lime juice and food coloring. Pour into baked pastry shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding sugar to taste.
Spread over filling.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 10 minutes or until meringue is browned.
Cool and chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: party cookies (m&m's)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together; add to egg and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Reserve remaining M&M's for decorating.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate tops of cookies with remaining M&M's. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into lightly greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: best ever gingerbread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; set aside.
Dissolve soda in 1/8 cup hot water.
Add to previous mixture.
Sift in flour and beat well.
Add boiling water.
Beat lightly and quickly pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil
brown
sugar,
butter,
syrup and salt 5 minutes. Remove from
heat
and add soda and butter flavoring and stir well. Pour
over
popcorn.
Mix
well.
Put in oven 1 hour at 200°. Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool and put in container.

title: pear honey
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick.
Pour in jars and seal.
I put mine in the jar, seal and cook in hot water bath for 15 or so minutes after boiling.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake inn 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla and pie filling. Mix with wooden spoon.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not remove until completely cool.

title: orange pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add orange juice. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Beat yolks with fork and add sugar.
Add to orange mixture.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites and sugar to make meringue.
Top pie and brown.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: In punch bowl, put half of torn up angel food cake, then pour 1 box (do not overbeat) pudding, 1 quart strawberries, 3 bananas and 1 container Cool Whip over that.
Repeat all layers and decorate with strawberries.
Enjoy!

title: nacho chili dip
directions: Put beans in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put cream cheese slices over chili, then cover with taco cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Serve with Fritos dipper chips.

title: brown sugar peanut brittle
directions: In a heavy 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, water and a dash of salt.
Cook and stir until sugars dissolve.
When syrup boils, stir frequently after mixture reaches thread stage. Add margarine when candy thermometer reaches 230°.
Add peanuts when temperature reaches soft crack stage (280°).
Stir constantly until temperature reaches hard crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in soda.
Mix well.

title: macaroni cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs and butter. Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Melt butter and drizzle over cracker crumbs.
Bake in oven, covered with foil, for 20 to 30 minutes. Remove foil to brown. Bake at 350°.

title: g. g. parker's clam pie
directions: Clean clams under cool water.
Open, keeping juice in pan. Add clams, water and butter; simmer about 5 minutes or until clams start to curl.
Transfer to buttered casserole dish.
Add biscuit topping (6 to 8 to cover clams) and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until biscuits are browned but not doughy underneath.

title: potato supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with crumb topping of corn flakes. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes in a long, shallow casserole dish. Serves 12 to 15.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Arrange chicken on foil lined cookie sheet sprayed with Pam. Brush chicken with olive oil and sprinkle seasonings on chicken to taste. Place in 450° oven and bake until chicken is golden brown.

title: envelope rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cool to lukewarm (105° to 115°). Add yeast mixture.
Add eggs.
Mix in 4 1/2 cups flour to form smooth dough (beat 50 to 100 strokes by hand).
If dough is too sticky, add more flour (it should not stick to sides).
Place in an oiled bowl and turn to grease top.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size.

title: sparkling strawberry punch
directions: Puree strawberries and lemonade in blender.
Pour mixture into chilled 6-quart punch bowl.
Add 7-Up, ginger ale, club soda, ice cubes and sugar.
Stir punch until sugar dissolves.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: marinade sauce for beef tenderloin
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over tenderloin and let stand at least 8 hours; turn meat several times while marinating.
Baste meat with sauce while baking.
Drippings can be used for gravy.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add water until visible.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Stir and serve.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Blend sugar with cornstarch, salt and grated rind and juice. Add boiling water.
Let cook long enough to cook the cornstarch; add the butter.
Serve warm over Cottage Pudding.

title: frozen roast
directions: On top of stove, heat the oil to sizzling in cast-iron Dutch oven with lid.
Season frozen roast with garlic powder, salt and pepper liberally.
Brown on all sides.
Add 1/2 cup of water, cover with lid and braise, adding water as necessary.
Cook until meat is tender, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove roast.
Put vegetables in Dutch oven.
Stir and cook until fork tender and caramelized.
Replace the roast in with the vegetables and continue cooking about 20 minutes more.
Remove meat and vegetables to a platter and from the drippings in bottom of Dutch oven make a rich brown gravy.
Thicken with cornstarch and a small amount of water.

title: country pork chop casserole
directions: Cover bottom of Dutch oven or electric skillet with shortening 1/8-inch deep.
Heat shortening.
Roll pork chops in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in shortening on both sides and remove.
Add onion and simmer until onion is clear.
Add potatoes (cut round ways).
Place pork chops on top of potatoes and add enough water until it can be seen up around potatoes.
Do not cover completely. Cover and cook at medium or low heat until water cooks down to a thick broth, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick and delicious watermelon rind pickles
directions: Cut rind of watermelon into 1-inch blocks.
Boil in salt water, 1/2 cup salt to 2 gallons of water, for 5 minutes or until tender. Drain, then soak and wash through 3 cold waters.
Drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar, cloves and cinnamon and cook until clear.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: dried beef chicken breasts
directions: Wrap each chicken breast in one piece of bacon.
Put dried beef on bottom and sides of baking dish.
Lay chicken on top.
Mix soup and sour cream.
(You can add a touch of milk, if desired.) Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: southern dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill for 1 hour.
Roll out dough thin and cut into 2-inch strips.
Make sure dough is well floured. Drop into boiling broth and cook until done.
Do not stir while they are cooking. They cook within 1 hour over medium heat.

title: baked crab salad
directions: Mix together and pour into casserole dish; sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake with cover at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and put casserole on broil for 3 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, soda and cloves.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with cold coffee. Stir in raisins, nuts and apples.
Bake in 6-inch tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yummy chocolate sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan over medium heat (or double boiler), heat ingredients until mixture is smooth and boils, stirring.
Makes 1 1/3 cup sauce.

title: wild rice pilaf
directions: Cook the bacon until it's nice and crisp.
Drain, cool, crumble and set aside.
In 2-3 Tbsp. of the bacon fat, cook the wild rice and mushrooms until the mushrooms are cooked through.

title: butter pecan turtles
directions: In a large bowl or food processor, combine flour, brown sugar and butter.
Mix at medium speed for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pat firmly into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans over crust.
Melt 2/3 cup butter in saucepan.
Stir in 1/2 cup packed brown sugar. Boil 1 minute.
Pour over pecans.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, or until crust is light golden brown.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with chips.
Allow chips to melt and swirl to cover. Cool.
Cut into 24 bars.

title: okra pilau
directions: Fry bacon until almost crisp in saucepan.
Add okra; fry until tender.
Add water, rice, salt and pepper.
Cover, turn heat very low.
Cook, stirring several times, for 1 hour or until rice is dry.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: carole's meat pies
directions: Brown and drain meat mixture.
Add soup and cheese.
Divide rolls.
Place meat mixture on crescent roll; seal edges.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with rice pilaf.

title: cream cheese sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, margarine, cream cheese, salt, almond extract, vanilla and egg yolk; blend well.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Refrigerate dough 2 hours for easier handling. Preheat oven to 375°.
On lightly floured surface, roll out dough 1/3 at a time to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes with lightly floured cookie cutters.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Leave cookies plain, or if desired, brush with slightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool for a minute or so, then carefully remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water, then stir in pie filling.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 2-inch baking dish and chill until partially set.
Dissolve the lemon Jell-O in remaining boiling water.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted butter together for crust.
Cook flour and milk until thick; let cool.
Mix sugar, shortening and 1 stick butter together until smooth.
Add cooked pudding; spread on crust.
Put pineapple on top of this, then put bananas on top of pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on this.
Sprinkle with pecans, coconut and cherries.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 2 cups hot water.
Add 7-Up; let gel partially.
Add apples, drained pineapple, marshmallows, bananas and nuts.
Gel.

title: pigs-n-a blanket
directions: Cut biscuits in 1/2; spread some cheese spread on it and wrap around a little sausage; repeat until all biscuits are done, then bake according to the directions on the can of biscuits.

title: canter meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour. Drain, let stand 5 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix both sugars, margarine and egg in mixing bowl with large spoon.
Stir together or sift flour, salt and soda; then stir into sugar mixture (dough will be stiff).
Stir in chips and nuts; then drop on cookie sheet (ungreased) by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake until light brown for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cookies cool slightly, then remove from cookie sheet with spatula onto paper towels or cookie racks to cool.
Store covered.

title: poor man's shrimp
directions: Mix ketchup and horseradish to your taste.
Pour over cream cheese and spread on crackers.

title: naturally sweet soft cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine raisins, dates, banana, peanut butter, water, egg and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Add oatmeal, flour, and baking soda.
Mix to blend thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto non-stick baking sheets or onto baking sheets sprayed with cooking spray.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes or until browned.
Cool on rack.
This recipe contains no added sugar.
The sweet taste comes from the fruit.
Each cookie contains 44 calories.
Two cookies count for one bread and one-half fat exchange.
One tablespoon of salad dressing can be used in place of the egg.
This recipe is great for diabetics.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening and cool.
Add sugar, molasses and eggs; beat well.
Mix together flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt. Add to first mixture; mix well and chill.
Roll into 1 inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Chop onion and bell pepper.
Saute in a small amount of drippings until cooked.
Combine cooked rice, shrimp, onion, bell pepper and the can of mushrooms in a large rectangular greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Stir in bottle of Thousand Island dressing.
Cover with strips of raw bacon.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Fluff with fork.
Serves 8.

title: steak bake
directions: Coat narrow strips of sirloin in seasoned flour.
Then brown in margarine.
Put in casserole dish.
Add onions, green pepper, tomatoes, mushrooms, molasses and soy sauce.
Mix well.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Stir in French-cut green beans.
Top with spoonfuls of Tangy Muffin Mix (recipe follows), sprinkled with sesame seed.

title: pineapple cream pie(sister lottie lambert's)
directions: Drain pineapple and set aside.
Save juice and add enough water to make one cup and set aside.
Beat egg yolks, then add sugar, salt and flour to make a paste.
Add milk, juice, oleo and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add crushed pineapple.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and put on top.
Bake in oven at 425° until brown.

title: cinnamon apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve 1 tablespoon cinnamon candies in boiling water.
Arrange apples in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour cinnamon flavored water over top.
Combine cake mix, brown sugar and butter in large bowl.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
(Mixture will be crumbly.) Sprinkle crumbs over apple slices.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
May be served with whipped topping.

title: quick cream cheese crescents
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
In large bowl, mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in hot water and cream cheese.
Mix in egg and only enough reserved flour to make soft dough.
On floured surface, knead 4 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half into a 10-inch circle.
Cut each circle into 6 wedges. Starting from wide ends, roll up to tip; seal points.
Shape into crescents and place on greased baking sheet; cover.
Place large shallow pan on counter; half fill with boiling water.
Place baking sheet over shallow pan; let dough rise 25 to 30 minutes. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Brush with melted margarine.
Remove from baking sheet; cool on wire rack.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Stir.
Add cranberries and juice.
Stir until well mixed.
Chill slightly until it begins to jell.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into large mold and refrigerate until set.

title: cranberry raspberry cheese mold
directions: Dissolve 1 package gelatin in 1 cup boiling water, stirring about 2 minutes.
Pour into blender.
Add cream cheese.
Blend on high until smooth.
Pour into 5-cup mold that has been greased. Chill until set, but not firm.

title: spaghetti soup
directions: Bring all ingredients, except spaghetti, to a boil.
Turn down heat; let simmer for about 45 minutes.
Break the spaghetti into about 2-inch pieces.
Parboil spaghetti; drain and add to broth mixture.
Simmer until done.

title: honey-glazed spareribs
directions: Have your butcher cut ribs down length of slab into two pieces so that each half is 2 to 3-inches wide.
Cut between the bones to make 6-inch pieces.
Trim excess fat from ribs.
Place ribs in heavy resealable plastic bag.
For marinade, combine 1/4 cup soy sauce, hoisin sauce, 2 tablespoons sherry, sugar, ginger, garlic and five-spice powder in small cup or bowl; mix well.
Pour over ribs.
Seal bag tightly; place in large bowl.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight, turning bag occasionally.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Line large baking pan with foil.
Place ribs on rack pan, reserving marinade.
Bake 30 minutes; turn ribs over.
Brush with marinade; continue baking 40 minutes or until ribs are tender when pierced with fork.

title: pasta bake
directions: Cook pasta.
Heat large frypan and add oil, beef or turkey and garlic.
Saute until meat is tender; drain excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients, except cheese, for topping and the pasta. Simmer until pasta is cooked.
Drain pasta and mix with sauce. Pour into 3-quart baking dish and bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes at 350° or until all is bubbly hot.
Enjoy!!!

title: creamy dill dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, stir until smooth. Cover and chill. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: dutch hay
directions: Cook ribs in water until done.
Remove meat from liquid. Bring to boil sauerkraut in its own juice.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Layer chicken breasts in baking dish.
Top with cheese slices. Mix together melted butter and prepared Stove Top stuffing mix. Spread over cheese and chicken.
Mix together milk and cream of mushroom soup; pour over top of Stove Top, cheese and chicken. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 375°.

title: no bake divinity
directions: Combine icing mix, sugar, vanilla and water in a small bowl. Beat at high speed until stiff peaks form.
Transfer mix to larger bowl and, at low speed, beat in confectioners sugar.
Fold in nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Top with nuts.
Allow to dry on top 12 hours, turning pieces over once or twice.
Store in a container.

title: cheese dip for vegetables
directions: Dissolve beef bouillon in small
amount
of
hot water.
Beat in softened cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add chopped onion. Refrigerate. Serve with raw cauliflower, cabbage, celery or carrots.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cut the chicken breasts into strips.
Cut the pepper into thin strips.
Heat the oil in a large skillet.
Add chicken; cook and stir until it is thoroughly browned.
Add the broccoli, red pepper and water chestnuts.
Cook and stir until tender-crisp.
Mix in broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, garlic powder and ginger into the mixture.
Bring to a boil; let it boil for 1 1/4 minutes.
Prepare the rice as directed on the package, omitting the margarine and salt.
Pour mixture over rice and serve.

title: fresh squeezed lemonade
directions: Combine water and sugar in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Pour sugar mixture into a pitcher; chill.
Add lemon juice to sugar mixture; stir well.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with lemon wedges, if desired.
Yields 1 quart (serving size:
1 cup).

title: cream of spinach soup
directions: Put spinach through sieve.
Add with onion to the cup of hot milk in saucepan.
Gradually stir in the thin white sauce, stirring until smooth.
Season with salt to taste and a dash of nutmeg.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients. Stir in pecans. Combine remaining ingredients; add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until tests done. Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove and let cool on wire racks.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash with salt. Drain and mash. Add other ingredients and pour into greased Pyrex (9 x 13-inch). Top with Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese roll
directions: Ingredients should be at room temperature.
Between wax paper, spread Velveeta until about 1/4-inch thick.
Mix cream cheese and onions and spread over Velveeta.
Layer peppers and black olives over cream cheese and onions.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Better if made up night before serving.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Peel potatoes and cut into thin slices. In a bowl, combine remaining ingredients; add potatoes and toss well.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Cook in boiling, salted water until tender; drain and mash.
Beat eggs; blend in flour, sugar, baking powder, eggplant and salt.
Drop by teaspoons in hot fat, turning to brown.

title: german potato salad
directions: In mixing bowl, add diced potatoes with skin still on them. Add eggs, celery salt, garlic salt, worcestershire sauce, mustard, onions and mayonnaise. Mix all ingredients well and serve. Best potato salad in town.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix hamburg, macaroni and sauce together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni slices.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Blend egg yolks, flour, sugar, cocoa and 1/2 cup milk to make paste.
Add remaining milk, oleo and vanilla.
Cook until thick. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: cheese roll-ups
directions: Remove crusts from bread and flatten bread with rolling pin. Place cheese slice at the edge of bread and roll up.
Brush with melted butter and place in oven until toasted.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, sunflower seeds, raisins, bacon and onions in a large bowl.
Mix together remaining ingredients and toss with broccoli mixture.
Chill until serving time.
Serves 6-8.

title: salsa
directions: Stir tomatoes, celery, onions and chilies until well mixed. Add tomato sauce until the right consistency.
Add Tabasco to taste.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Place in casserole dish.
Dump mushroom soup in.
Cover and fill dish with Tater Tots.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until Tater Tots are done.

title: apple nut salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix together last 3 and toss over the first mix. If you wish you can leave out the celery and add more apples.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs which have been beaten until lemon colored.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and light bread.
Add onion, sage, pepper, salt, poultry seasoning and onion soup mix.
Stir in eggs, celery soup, chicken soup and enough broth to make a moist dressing. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage and pepper sandwiches
directions: In medium skillet over medium -high heat, cook sausage and pepper until sausage is browned, stirring to separate meat. Drain off fat. Add soup. Reduce heat to low and heat through. Divide meat mixture among rolls. Serve.

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease 1 (9-inch) spring-form pan.
Dust with graham cracker crumbs.
Sieve cottage cheese into large mixing bowl.
Add cream cheese; beat with high speed of electric mixer until well blended. Beating at high speed, blend in sugar and then eggs.
Reduce speed to low; add cornstarch, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Add melted oleo and sour cream.
Blend well on low speed.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Blend all together.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: corn biscuits
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Melt	butter	in 10 x 15-inch jelly roll
pan.	Cool slightly.	Meanwhile, mix Bisquick and corn only until mixed.
Do not beat.	Pat dough onto a floured board into a rectangle about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into fingers about 1
x 3-inch.
Put each biscuit into the pan, turning so that each finger
is	coated with the melted butter.	Bake in 400° oven
minutes
or
until	golden.
These easy biscuits are crisp and delicious.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and oil.
Put in rest of ingredients.
Bake in tube pan or oblong pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: t.v. snacks
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together until boiling, then add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: triple corn fritters
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup, level off.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, sugar and salt.
In large bowl, combine eggs, milk, oil and cream-style corn.
Blend in dry ingredients stirring just until moistened.
Stir in whole kernel corn.
In deep fat fryer or heavy saucepan, drop batter by tablespoonfuls and fry in 2 to 3 inches of hot fat (365°) for 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.
Serve warm.
Makes 28 fritters.

title: raisin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook raisins and water, covered, until tender (about 5 minutes).
Stir in mixture of sugar, sweeteners and flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until boiling. Boil 1 minute.
Pour hot filling in pastry lined pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Combine shortening, milk and eggs. Add to flour and cornmeal. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 450°.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Form cheese mixture into a log and roll in pecans.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Just before serving, add 2-quarts of ginger ale.
Serves 30.

title: anna's cabbage
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch pan with cover, all ingredients plus salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour.
Stir a couple of times. Add more oleo if larger head.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed.
Add one can tuna or you can use 1 cup cooked chicken or ham or even a can of salmon.
Add mushroom soup.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°
for 25 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Heat milk
almost
to boiling.	Mix in the sugar, salt, vanilla and
eggs.	Pour
into
pastry shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at
475° for 5 minutes, then 425° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: banana frosted layer cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add vanilla.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil oleo, water and cocoa (until oleo melts).
Cool 5 minutes.
Sift and add flour, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Pour into greased 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cocoa peanut brittle
directions: About 2 hours before serving or up to 1 week ahead, lightly grease large cookie sheet and set aside.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, beat sugar, corn syrup and heavy cream to boiling, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in peanuts.

title: spanish corn bread
directions: Grease a 10 3/4 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Add liquids to dry ingredients; blend in corn.
Add cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top and add chili powder, also.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: quick orange streusel cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; make a well and add wet ingredients. Stir just until lumpy.
Put in a 10-inch pie pan.

title: connecticut yankee strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients and set aside, then combine strawberries and rhubarb with flour mixture.
Be certain it mixes well and let stand for about 20 minutes.
When ready, pour filling into 9-inch pastry shell.
Dot it with 1 tablespoon of butter or margarine.
Cover with pie crust and bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Chop cucumbers and peppers very fine; separate.
Add all ingredients together; mix well.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Put into pint jars.
This is good on hot dogs and potato salad.
I put it in deviled eggs.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, salt and soda; add buttermilk, oil, eggs and corn.
Beat and mix well.
Stir in jalapenos, green pepper and onions.
Grease 9 x 14-inch baking dish with bacon drippings; heat well.
Pour in half of batter; sprinkle with half of cheese and repeat.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: old-fashioned hermits
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg and flavorings; mix well.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with apple juice (beginning and ending with flour) and mix well after each addition.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on cookie sheets sprayed with Pam or vegetable cooking spray.
Press a raisin in center of each cookie.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly on cookie sheets before removing.
Makes 56 cookies.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook broccoli.
Follow directions on package.
While noodles are cooking, heat milk and herb mix and butter.
While butter is melting, place chicken in greased baking dish.
Add all ingredients.
Mix together.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread ingredients in layers in order given in dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until it tests done and is brown on top.
If the berries are frozen when put in baking dish, the baking time will be increased.

title: pickled watermelon rind
directions: Remove all hard green outer shell of watermelon rind, leaving only the white rind.
Dice white rind to make 12 cups.
Combine salt, water and diced rind in large pan.
Soak for 1/2 hour. Drain the rind and rinse with water several times.
Place rind in large kettle.
Cover with water.
Cook over medium heat until tender, making sure rind is always covered with water.
When rind is tender, add vinegar, sugar, nutmeg, ginger, cloves and cinnamon to rind and water.
Cook again until rind is transparent again. Make sure rind is always covered with water.
When rind has cooled, place in jars and refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: marinated carrots
directions: In a bowl mix all ingredients except carrots.
Drain cooked carrots and pour into mixture.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: summer vegetable casserole
directions: Butter baking dish.
Layer squash, tomatoes, pepper and onions (sliced thin).
Dot with butter, salt and pepper.
Top with slices of cheese.
Continue to top of dish, ending with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until fork-tender.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut a slit down the length of the frankfurter.
Fill slit with 1/2 a slice of cheese.
Starting with the wide end, roll frankfurter in crescent roll.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a heavy 4-quart pan, combine sugar, syrup and water.
Boil rapidly over high heat until it spins a thread.
Add pecans. Continue cooking until it turns a light brown.
Remove from heat. Add oleo and vanilla.
Stir.
Add soda.
Stir.
While it is still bubbling, pour out on 2 greased cookie sheets as thinly as possible.
Let cool.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni. Drain. Cool and add other ingredients.

title: tuna noodle casserole(serves 4)
directions: Saute onion in butter in small, flat (stove top-proof) casserole dish.
Add tuna, breaking up meat and mixing with onions.
Add cooked noodles.
Mix.
Add soup and mix well.
Add milk to moisten.
(You don't want to see liquid in bottom of dish.)
Mix well.
Add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese; mix well. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese over top of mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly. Recipe may be doubled.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening (Crisco) and sweet potatoes. Add sweet potato mixture and cut in with a pastry blender.
Turn onto a floured surface.
Knead lightly.
Roll with rolling pin a 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out with a biscuit cutter.
Put on a baking sheet.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes or a little longer.
Check when done.
Biscuits will be lightly brown.
Remove from baking as soon as possible.

title: no. 3 tropical treat punch non-alcoholic drink
directions: Combine all 3 ingredients.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: apple chili
directions: Brown meat and onion until almost done.
Drain fat; add rest of the ingredients and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: margaret's honey bun cake
directions: Pour half of cinnamon mixture over batter in pan.
Pour rest of batter over mixture.
Add rest of cinnamon mixture.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice, vinegar and salt.
Chill and when slightly thickened, add pineapple, celery and nuts.
Chill.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Melt butter in frypan.
Add chops.
Add onions and celery; cook until onions turn clear.
Add diced bread, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Arrange chops in baking dish.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: watercress soup
directions: Melt butter, cook and stir onions and celery in butter until onions are tender.
Stir in chicken broth.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Simmer until celery is tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in watercress and potato flakes.
Heat just until watercress is wilted, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool slightly. Pour watercress mixture in blender and blend until smooth.
Stir in pepper and cream.
Heat until boiling.
Serve hot or cold.

title: broth for colds
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add all ingredients; simmer for 5 or 10 minutes.
Drink 1 cup 4 times a day.

title: cheese and spinach pasta
directions: Combine egg, sour cream, milk, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, onion, salt and pepper; mix well.
Stir in Monterey Jack cheese. Cook spinach according to package directions; drain.
Add spinach and cooked spaghetti (or noodles); mix well.
Put into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until top is browned.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add eggs, vanilla, then baking soda and baking powder, then sour cream alternately with flour.

title: chicken saltimbocca
directions: Skin, half and bone chicken breasts.
Pound lightly with a meat mallet, forming a rectangle, about 1/8-inch thick.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Place a ham slice and a cheese slice on each cutlet, trimming to fit within 1/4-inch of edges.
Top with some chopped tomato; sprinkle lightly with sage.
Fold in sides; roll up jelly roll style, pressing to seal.
Combine crumbs, cheese and parsley.
Dip chicken in butter, then roll in crumbs.
Bake in a shallow baking pan in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove to a serving platter.
Stir mixture remaining in pan until smooth; spoon over chicken.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg, water and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oats, nuts, raisins or chocolate chips.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: cherry surprise balls
directions: Drain cherries well.
Mix butter, coconut, sugar and vanilla together.
Wrap around cherries, then roll into graham cracker crumbs.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars. Mix in eggs and vanilla. Stir together flour, salt, soda and spices. Fold into creamed mixture. Stir in oats. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: old fashion boil dinner
directions: Put in a large pan of cold water 1 smoked picnic ham shoulder. Wash cabbage, chopped in fourths.
Put in the pan.
Put clean potatoes that are cut in halves in, then carrots cut in halves and onions cut in fourths.
Boil this for 2 hours.
Serve with homemade bread and a slice of pie.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool. Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and frozen whipped topping; spread over pretzel crust.
Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water; stir in strawberries.
Cool until mixture begins to congeal. Spoon over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Mix cake mix, melted margarine and egg together; press into a long cake pan. Beat cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar together; pour over cake mixture. Bake about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave fruit and nut chews
directions: In a 2-quart glass measure, cook margarine on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, until melted.
Stir in apricots and sugar, then egg. Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in cereal and pecans.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, pudding mix and water.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Chill and garnish as desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: grilled green tomatoes
directions: Rinse the tomatoes and pat dry.
Slice crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Brush slices with oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
On an open grill over medium coals, grill tomatoes for approximately 4 minutes or until lightly grill marked and tender.

title: sun-maid classic sour cream raisin pie
directions: Beat
eggs, sour cream, sugar, vanilla, salt and nutmeg together.
Blend
well.
Add
raisins.
Pour
into	pie shell; bake
below
oven
center at 375° for 40 minutes or until done (just until set).
Cool and top with sour cream (spoonful to a serving), if desired.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix by directions on box and pat out in well-greased pizza pan.
Bake and cool.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Fry bacon crisp and drain.
Put all in crock-pot and cook slow about 2 hours.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, over medium heat, heat cranberries, sugar and one cup of water to boiling.
Stir frequently.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Yields 7 cups.

title: pineapple custard pie
directions: Blend 1/3 cup sugar with cornstarch and crushed pineapple (with juices). Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and clear. Cool.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt over medium heat first 4 ingredients.
Remove from heat. Add powdered sugar; beat with mixer until smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups pecans and the vanilla.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: sunday fried chicken
directions: Coat chicken with
combined flour and seasoning.
Brown on all sides in
hot
Crisco.
Reduce
heat and cook uncovered for about 45 minutes, until chicken is tender.

title: sausage and bean soup
directions: Place chickpeas in 4 cups of water; cover and boil for two minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand for one hour.
Add sausage, ham, bacon, onions, salt and 4 more cups water.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until chickpeas are tender.
Add potatoes and simmer 20 minutes.
Add cabbage and simmer 10 minutes more.
Makes about eight servings.

title: ham and spinach rolls
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and mustard.
In medium bowl, combine 1/2 of soup mixture, rice, onion, eggs and flour.
Mix well and place 2 tablespoons mixture on each slice of ham.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in baking dish.
(I use Pam first.)
Top with remaining soup mixture and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.

title: easy tamales
directions: Boil pork until meat shreds off bone (several hours).
Place flour in large frypan and brown.
Remove from heat and let cool approximately 20 minutes.
Add chili powder.
Mix in chili sauce and garlic.
Mix until smooth.
Add water and salt and simmer 5 minutes over low heat.
Add shredded meat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Chill pie shell.
Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla. Gradually stir in milk.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: rice-a-l'orange
directions: Drain pineapple slices, reserving juice.
Chop pineapple and set aside.
Saute peppers and onion in 1 tablespoon melted butter, in a saucepan, until tender.
Add orange juice and bring to a boil.
Add rice, remaining 3 tablespoons butter, chopped pineapple, salt and curry powder.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes, stirring once.
Garnish with red and green pepper strips.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: curried eggs
directions: Combine soup, milk and curry powder.
Let this come to a boil and then add the sliced eggs.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: crock-pot potato soup
directions: Add ingredients except evaporated milk into a crock-pot. Cover and cook on high for 3 to 4 hours or on low for 10 to 12 hours.
During the last hour, stir in the evaporated milk.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit punch #2
directions: Mix juices and water.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Serves 12 to 16.

title: vegi-bars
directions: *Can use any other vegetable combo.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a small bowl.
Cut in chilled butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Stir milk into flour mixture, mixing until a soft dough forms.
Knead briefly until dough forms a ball.
Divide dough in half.
Pat dough halves into 2 greased 8-inch layer cake pans. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat sugar, margarine, corn syrup, salt and eggs with hand beater in medium bowl.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until set.
Yields 8 servings, 515 calories per serving.

title: walnut glory cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Beat egg whites in large mixing bowl until soft mounds form.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar. Continue beating until very stiff, straight peaks form.
Combine egg yolks, vanilla and 3/4 cup sugar in small mixing bowl.
Beat until thick and lemon-colored.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Fold batter gently but thoroughly into egg whites using wire whip or rubber spatula.
Fold in walnuts.
Turn into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.
Invert immediately.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
Frost with a vanilla glaze, sprinkle with confectioners sugar or serve with whipped cream.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: home cleaner
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add water and blend thoroughly.
Can be used to remove grease and other stains from floors, painted surfaces and most appliances.

title: raisin and carrot salad
directions: Mix together and chill until ready to serve.

title: special cole slaw
directions: Drain pineapple and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Bring to a boil and pour on gelatin.
Add 1 cup of water and salt. Refrigerate until solid.
Beat until stiff.
Add whipped cream and mix thoroughly.
Add cabbage and pineapple.
Mix well.
Let stand overnight before serving.

title: no-fat chocolate sauce
directions: In a saucepan stir together sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and milk. Cook and stir constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm or cold over any dessert.
Can be refrigerated, covered, for a week.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Blend all ingredients well.
Pour in pan and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: velvet fudge cake
directions: Blend ingredients at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pans.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and margarine.
Add eggs; cream again.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, baking soda and salt.
Mix and add flour. After dropping on cookie sheet, press flat with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in flavoring.
Add dry ingredients. Fold in fruit and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 325° or less for about 4 hours or until a toothpick comes out clean.
This is very good.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash fresh cranberries and pick out any soft ones.
Put through a food chopper or processor.
Put sugar over them and a little orange juice.
Let sit awhile.

title: hungarian pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Line baking sheet with paper towels, two layers is best.
Wash, peel and coarsely grate potatoes and onion.
Stir in egg, flour, salt and pepper.
Heat 1/2 inch oil in large skillet over moderately high heat.
Drop heaping tablespoons of potato mixture into oil.
Flatten slightly with spatula and fry about 4 minutes, until edges are crispy.
Turn and cook about 1 minute more.
Remove to baking sheet and keep warm in oven. Repeat until all mixture is used.
Dollop on sour cream and pass applesauce.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: In one bowl, mix egg white and water. Beat slightly with fork to mix well. Pour 4 cups pecans into this mixture and mix until it is all soaked onto pecans.

title: cranberry cooler
directions: Combine lemon, orange and cranberry juices and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved; add sparkling water.
Pour into an ice filled pitcher or punch bowl.
Garnish with fruit slices.

title: orange spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients together and store in container.
For serving 1, mix 2 to 3 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water; or mix 2 cups for 1 gallon.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat pudding and milk together with mixer until thick (about 2 minutes). By hand, gently fold in Cool Whip. Place one layer of crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan. (Leave crackers whole.)
Spread half of the pudding mixture on crackers.
Repeat layers.
Finish with another layer of crackers.
Top with frosting.

title: hidden valley green pea salad
directions: Make
dressing of sour cream, Ranch
dressing,	mustard and garlic; shake well and pour over vegetables.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce as desired.
In a very large bowl, layer the following: lettuce, tomatoes, kidney beans, shredded cheese and hamburger. Add Doritos chips and toss.
Now, add the Wish-Bone dressing. Serves 4 to 6.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Cook sugar, cinnamon, vanilla, water and butter until mixture spins a thread.
Pour in nuts; stir quickly.
Turn out onto waxed paper.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add additional amounts of spices as needed for personal taste.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until medium cooked.
Rinse in cold water.
Arrange layers of carrots, onions and peppers in bowl.
Bring to a boil the remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Refrigerate; will keep for weeks.

title: tomato-clam cocktail
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Makes 3 cups, about 44 calories per cup.

title: magic marshmallow puffs
directions: Roll marshmallows in melted margarine.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Roll marshmallows in sugar mixture.
Wrap crescent triangle (one roll) around each marshmallow, pinching edges tightly to seal.
Dip in margarine; place in muffin pan (ungreased).
Place foil under pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden.
Remove immediately and drizzle with glaze.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Place under lock and key if you expect to save some for yourself!

title: microwave perky nachos
directions: Place a layer of tortilla chips close together on a waxed paper-lined 10-inch plate.
Sprinkle with chopped chilies and black olives.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: old fashioned creamy pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla and pecans. Cook over low heat about 30 to 40 minutes, stirring constantly.
When a hard ball can be formed when small amount is dropped in cold water, add vanilla.
Remove from heat and place pot in 2-inches of cold water in sink.
Add pecans and continue stirring until creamy and has become semi-glossy.
Spoon out onto waxed paper and let cool. Using a tablespoon, this will yield approximately 75 pralines.

title: cabbage buns
directions: Saute the onions, celery and green peppers.
Add to the fried hamburgers.
Add 2 cups sliced cabbage.
Simmer a few minutes.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown meat and follow directions on taco mix.
After it has cooked 10 to 15 minutes, add pinto beans.
Combine water and salsa.

title: cucumber sunomono
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin.
Salt over each layer.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: peach aspic
directions: Soften plain gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Dissolve plain and peach flavored gelatin in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Add orange juice, rind and lemon juice.
Add mashed peaches, sweetened to taste.
Pour into a 6-cup ring mold and chill until set.
Serve with Cream Cheese Dressing.

title: onion-roasted potatoes
directions: In large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Shake or toss until well coated.
Empty in pan or baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are brown.

title: choco-moist cake(fruit cocktail cake)
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine all ingredients except the chocolate chips and nuts.
After pouring batter into the pan, sprinkle the chocolate chips and nuts over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not cut until completely cold. Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: spinach-cauliflower toss
directions: Mix fresh chopped cucumbers, fresh chopped tomatoes and chopped fine onions.
Mix with fresh lemon juice, little sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix with dill weed, tarragon, garlic powder, marjoram and cumin.

title: broccoli with mushroom cheese sauce
directions: Fry onion in butter, then place frozen broccoli in and cook on low fire.
Melt in saucepan the mushroom soup and garlic cheese; add the mushrooms.
Pour over the broccoli in a casserole dish. Fifteen minutes before serving, sprinkle with bread crumbs and pass in oven.
Can be made ahead of time and put in refrigerator.

title: brian and lisa's painted pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chops in a shallow baking dish. Season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cover and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
On each chop place 1 tablespoon brown sugar, 1 tablespoon ketchup and 1 slice of fresh lemon.
Return to oven, uncovered, for about 15 minutes.

title: chip bean dip
directions: Spread avocado over bean dip.
Spread sour cream and taco mix over avocado.
Sprinkle green onions over spread.
Spread grated cheese on top of spread.
Spread tomatoes on top.
Spread sliced olives on top.

title: cheeseburger pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch deep pie pan.
Brown beef, onion, salt, pepper and seasoned salt.
Drain and spread in pie pan.
Mix milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth and pour over meat.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with sliced tomatoes and Cheddar cheese and bake 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Let cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: bran muffins
directions: Using very large bowl, mix dry ingredients first.
Add oil, eggs and buttermilk.
(Can be stored in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.)
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a paper bag.
Add meat and shake to coat.
Reserve flour mixture.
Heat fat or oil in heavy kettle and brown meat on all sides.
Remove meat.
Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add beef broth, 1/2 cup water, tomatoes, salt, pepper, bay leaf, caraway seed and cook until tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Blend 3 tablespoons flour and 1/2 cup water.
Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Toss cooked noodles with butter and serve with goulash.
Serves 6.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Cut up fruit as needed.
Sweeten with honey and a little sugar. Also use 1 small can chunk pineapple in own juice.
Mix all together.

title: broccoli elegant
directions: Cook broccoli on stove top or microwave.
Mix soup and milk in saucepan.
Stir in broccoli and olives.
Heat through.

title: bechamel sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour.
Reduce heat; add seasoning and liquid, stirring until smooth.

title: one minute cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, oleo and vanilla; bring to a boil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Then mix oats with that.
Drop from teaspoon onto platter and chill.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients together and form balls and freeze on tray.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Add enough water to make a gallon.

title: rotterdam liver pate
directions: *Make with 3 tablespoons flour, 3 tablespoons butter and 1 cup of milk.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Mix crumbs and melted butter together.
Press into 10-inch pie plate.
Bake into preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce to 325°.
Combine milk, eggs, Worcestershire sauce, salt and cheeses.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Cut up bacon and fry with onion until brown.
Drain.
Spread bacon and onion in baked crust.
Pour in egg mixture.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.
Make sure it is set in center.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Then mix the next 4 ingredients in a separate bowl.
Next, mix all this with flour and salt.
When ball form, let rise.
Roll out on floured board. Sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Roll up jelly roll style and slice.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sugar-free pineapple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie shell. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oleo.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour in 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
For 10-inch pie, double recipe.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix in sifted flour.
Add 7-Up and orange juice. Add flavoring last.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare and cook yellow cake as directed on box in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool a little.
While still warm, mix together pina colada mix and condensed milk.
Punch holes in warm cake and pour mixture over it.
(It looks awful, but just wait.)
Put in refrigerator and let cool for 30 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip and then sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate for 2 hours and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

Heat oil in nonstick pan. Add mushrooms, cooking over high heat until mushrooms are browned. Add turkey and cook until browned. Add onions, garlic and wine, cooking until wine evaporates. Add tomatoes, basil, oregano, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook the lasagna strips.
Lightly grease a 2-quart oblong baking dish. Place a layer of lasagna noodles on bottom.
Beat the Ricotta cheese with the warm milk and add a little fresh parsley.

Spread 1/3 of the cheese mixture over the noodles. Spread some of the tomato sauce over the cheese and sprinkle 1/4 of the Parmesan cheese over the tomato sauce. Repeat, ending with a layer of noodles.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese and pour the melted butter over the entire casserole. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: garden herb pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Put noodles in a bowl, then add broccoli, tomatoes, water chestnuts, onion and olives.

title: sugar free cranberry sauce
directions: Combine water and cranberries in medium saucepan. Boil gently, uncovered, until all cranberry skins pop, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and mash slightly. Add Equal and chill.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all well, bake in a preheated oven at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Add egg. Beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to cream mixture.
Mix until just blended.
Drop by tablespoons onto a cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly in a criss-cross pattern with a fork.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes, or until beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet.
Remove and cool completely.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Mix with enough mayonnaise to stick together.
Serve on lettuce, if desired.

title: cookies and cream(better than !)
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Reserve some crumbs for the top.
Pat the rest in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat pudding, milk and coloring until thick.
Add softened ice cream and beat.
Pour over crumbs. Spread whipped topping on top and sprinkle on the rest of crumbs. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In buttered pan, place the
uncooked rice.
Empty soup in bowl and add 1/2 cup water for each can.
Mix soup, water and pour over rice.
Add almonds.
Salt and pepper chicken and dip pieces in melted margarine and place on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours or bake at 350° for a shorter time or until chicken is golden on top.

title: orange french toast
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place bread slices in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: In large bowl, cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and 1 egg at a time, beating after each.
Stir in flour on low speed.
Spoon mixture into 10-inch tube pan. (Can't use regular Bundt pan.)
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours. I usually go around mine with a knife.
Shake and turn out within 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits(good for breakfast)
directions: Use Bisquick biscuit recipe on package.
Add sugar, cinnamon and one medium-size sweet potato which has been cooked in microwave or in oven and mashed.
Pat out dough with extra flour to keep from sticking and cut into biscuits.
Bake in greased iron skillet at 400° for approximately 12 minutes. Serve with butter, sorghum, syrup or honey.

title: blueberry-banana cream pie
directions: Mix Dream Whip, milk and sugar until thick and blend in cream cheese. Alternate layers of bananas and cream cheese (B-C-B-C); leave a well in center of pie
or heap sides with cream. Fill in center of pie with blueberry pie filling. "Refrigerate."

title: golden rice bake
directions: Saute onion in water.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered casserole.
If desired, layer with Cheddar cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen cucumber salad
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let mixture soak 3 hours. In a saucepan, warm the vinegar and sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Drain cucumbers and add to vinegar mixture.
Ladle into plastic freezer containers and freeze.
When ready to use, defrost and serve chilled.
Yield:
1 1/2 quarts.

title: philly fudge balls
directions: Combine ingredients.
Form into balls and roll into coconut, if desired.
Keep refrigerated.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water.
Drain well.
Add enough milk to cover and stir constantly while cooking to keep from sticking.
Add cheese, salt, pepper and bacon fat.
When cheese is well-melted, remove and cool.
Add celery and eggs.
Mix well with mayonnaise and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix oats, flour and brown sugar. Add nuts. Cut in butter or margarine with a pastry blender or fork until crumbly.
Place half of this mixture in a greased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Cover with uncooked rhubarb which has been mixed with remaining ingredients. Top with other half of oat mixture.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve warm.
Cut into squares.
This may be served with ice cream.

title: grape marmalade
directions: Wash grapes and pull off stems.
Do not hull.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Do not add water.
If it is not too thick, boil 5 more minutes.
Run through sieve to remove seeds and put in small sterilized jars.
Seal with wax.

title: christmas rice
directions: Combine rice, soup, pimento, water, green pepper and onion in casserole; mix well.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until rice is tender.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pans.
Put sugar, shortening, egg whites, vanilla and milk into a large mixing bowl. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into prepared pans and bake at 350° until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean or about 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with Seven Minute Icing and coconut.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in oblong baking dish.
Pour soups over chicken. Mix dressing according to directions, substituting chicken broth for water.
Spread this over soup and chicken.
Bake in a 300° oven until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all by hand, then add blueberries last. Mix well. Bake in muffin pan at 350° for 25 minutes. Yield 12 muffins.

title: baker's clay decorations(inedible)
directions: Combine flour and salt in a large bowl.
Gradually add water until mixture is a putty-like consistency.
Knead dough for 5 minutes or until ingredients are thoroughly blended.
Lay out a sheet of waxed (or freezer) paper.
Sprinkle with flour.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a cookie cutter (dip in flour if it sticks).
Make a hole with a straw or skewer.
Lift with a narrow spatula and place on
a rack.
Air dry for 48 hours at room temperature.
Can be painted when dry.
Store in dry place.

title: french onion soup
directions: Stock:
Place 5 pounds of bones in roasting pan.
Roast bones for 2 hours at 425°, uncovered.
Place bones in large soup pot. Add 1 quart of water for every pound of bones.
Add chopped celery, chopped carrots, 2 chopped onions and all of the onion skins from the 5 pounds of onions (skins add color).
Bring to heavy boil.
Add 1/2 dozen peppercorns and simmer for 8 or 9 hours.
Do not salt.
Strain stock and return stock to pot.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream oleo and shortening together. Add sugar and eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla, eggs and the last of the flour.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut off stem end of each pepper.
Remove seed.
Cook peppers in water for 5 minutes and drain.
Cook and stir ground meat and onion in medium skillet until onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in salt, garlic salt, rice and 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce; heat through.
Lightly stuff each pepper. Stand peppers in an ungreased dish, pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover; bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer in order listed, using about 1/3 of each ingredient in "first round" and the remainder of each ingredient in the "second round" of layers, always beginning with cake crumbs and ending with coconut.

title: garlic shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Slice peppers.
Set aside dry ingredients.
In a large frying pan, melt butter.
Add garlic and peppers.
Cook on medium heat until soft.
Put water on for pasta and, once boiling, add pasta to water.
Place shrimp in frying pan; stir-fry with peppers until shrimp turn pink.
Add dry ingredients; mix.
Serve shrimp mixture over fettucini.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherries in the snow cake
directions: Cut cake into bite size pieces.
Place 1/2 of the cake in dish.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Put 1/2 of this mixture over cake.
Add other 1/2 of cake, then the remainder of cheese mixture.
Top with pie filling. Chill and serve.

title: strawberry rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix until crumbly flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Press 1/2 of mixture in bottom of 9-inch pan.
Mix and stir until thick and clear (about 5 minutes) sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla.
Mix and place rhubarb and strawberries in pan. Pour liquid over rhubarb and strawberries.
Top with rest of the crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork bar-b-stew
directions: In a heavy Dutch oven or soup pot, lightly brown the pork in the oil.
Add the onion soup, 1 1/4 cups water, lemon juice and salt.
Simmer, covered, for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cabbage, carrots, green pepper strips and barbecue sauce with additional 1 cup water.
Cover and increase heat to medium.
Continue cooking for about 15 minutes longer or until mixture is slightly thickened.

title: p'nut kiddie cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet! That's all!
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: dog biscuits(for sam!)
directions: Combine flours, milk powder, oats, cornmeal and sugar.
Cut in shortening so the mixture is crumbly.
Stir in egg.
Stir bouillon in hot water until dissolved.
Slowly add to flour mixture.
Form a dough ball and knead 5 minutes.
Divide dough in half and roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Make cutouts or 5 dozen nuggets.
Place on plate and microwave on Medium for 5 to 10 minutes, until firm and dry to touch.
Rotate plate every 2 minutes and turn shapes over when halfway done.
Cool and shapes will turn crisp as they cool.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen cutouts.

title: sweet and sour brisket
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, put onions and garlic in bottom.
Place brisket on top.
Mix all ingredients in bowl and pour over brisket.
Cover; roast in 350° oven until tender, approximately 4 hours.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: buckeye's chocolate balls
directions: Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Mix rest of ingredients by hand and shape in balls the size of walnuts. Insert toothpicks into top of balls.
Dip into melted chocolate. Place on wax paper to cool on toothpick end.

title: onion meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, onion soup mix, milk and egg.
Press firmly into ungreased loaf pan.
Loosen edges with a spatula and unmold into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour or spoon over meat.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Makes 8 servings.

title: candy from potatoes
directions: Mash a cold boiled potato and work in confectioners sugar and vanilla until desired consistency.
Press the mixture down flat and spread with peanut butter.
Roll up as a jelly roll or roll into balls and dip in melted chocolate.
Real good, don't knock until you try it.

title: raspberry champagne punch
directions: Use another package of raspberries to make a large floating ice cube.
Serves 30.

title: cherry fruit salad
