directions: Blend milk and cherry pie filling. Add crushed pineapple (drained), vanilla and nuts. Blend in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and put chips on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, salt and nuts; set aside.
Combine oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add to dry mixture.
Do not overmix.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients and fold in egg whites, beaten dry.
Fry in deep fat, dropping from a teaspoon.

title: soda cracker cookies
directions: Boil for 3 minutes the milk and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package and mix with celery, onion, cheese and mayo.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1 tube crushed Ritz crackers and 1 stick melted margarine or butter.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: bugle munchies
directions: Fill Bugles with peanut butter; cake decorating bag works well.
Melt almond bark and dip filled Bugle in almond bark.

title: congealed peach salad
directions: Mix peach juice and jello. Heat to dissolve, let cool. Mix buttermilk and Cool Whip. Cut peaches with fork. Add peaches to Cool Whip and buttermilk mixture, then add to jello. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls into bottom of 9 x 12-inch greased baking pan.
Brown sausage; drain grease.
Spread potatoes on top of rolls.
Sprinkle sausage on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top of sausage.
Mix eggs with milk.
Pour on top of layered mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: apple crunch
directions: Combine all ingredients and sprinkle over an 8 1/2 x 13-inch glass dish with raw, sliced apples.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven until the apples are fully cooked.

title: spiced apple cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In small saucepan, cover raisins with water. Bring to boiling, remove from heat. Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Drain. Meanwhile, in larger bowl, beat shortening and brown sugar. Beat egg and milk. Stir together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, cloves and nutmeg. Add to shortening mixture. Beat well. Stir in nuts, apple and raisins. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8-10 minutes. Yield: 3 1/2 to 4 doz.

title: whole wheat caramel rolls
directions: Grease 9-inch square pan.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine 1/2 cup all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, sugar, salt and yeast; blend well.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Prepare graham cracker crust by combining crumbs, 1 stick butter and sugar. Prepare the following layers:

title: sukiyaki
directions: Brown steak (sliced thin and cut in 1 x 3-inch strips) in margarine.
Add soy sauce, sherry, beef broth and sugar.
Cover skillet and cook for 10 minutes.
Slice onions thinly.
Wash and slice mushrooms.
Slice celery.
Drain liquids from 1 can bamboo shoots and water chestnuts.
Add to browned steak with mushrooms, onions and celery.
Cook, uncovered, until mixture is heated through.
The vegetables should retain some crispness.
Serve with fluffy rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy yogurt-mint dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl, stirring well with a wire whisk.
Cover and chill.
Serve over salad greens or fresh fruit.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Saute onion.
Mix with other ingredients.
Shape into croquettes and fry or bake until browned.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thin; add brown sugar, milk, flour, vanilla and butter.
Add chopped pecan.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into walnut size balls and place on cookie sheet.
Cover and freeze.
Bake still frozen at 350° for 15 minutes.
Excellent hors d'oeuvre.

title: vickie's delicious hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer gently for about 5 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onion in a frypan.
Drain well.
Combine all ingredients, except pasta and pepper in a large pot.
Simmer, covered, for at least 2 hours.
Add pasta and simmer 15 minutes. Season with pepper.
Makes 10 servings.
Great for holidays; everyone can help themselves if you are busy.

title: fruit cake
directions: Line angel food tube with brown (sacks) paper.
Cut all fruit and nuts into small pieces.
Add dry ingredients; mix.
Beat eggs and vanilla.
Pour over mixture; mix well.
Pour into pan and bake 2 hours at 250°.

title: microwave chicken 'n rice casserole
directions: Mix soups and water together.
Add rice.
Pour into deep baking dish (8 x 8-inch Pyrex).
Cover with wax paper or plastic wrap.
Cook in radar range (covered) on Full power for 4 minutes. Place pieces of chicken on rice mixture.
Cover again and cook on Full power 18 to 20 minutes.
Turn chicken over 1 or 2 times during cooking.

title: naval academy potato salad
directions: Make sauce with vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add potatoes, celery, pimentos, sugar, pickle relish and mayonnaise.
Garnish with eggs and paprika. Chill.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: After popping corn, place into a large brown grocery bag.
Do not salt.
Combine brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart microwave bowl.
Bring to a boil, then cook for 2 more minutes on High in microwave.
Stir in soda, then pour on top of corn in bag.
Close bag and shake.
Cook in microwave 1 1/2 minutes more; shake and repeat.
Pour into pan and let cool.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Add cornbread
mix
to other ingredients, one at a time (mixture will be thick).
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cook on stove or in slow cooker on low until melted together.

title: meatballs
directions: Brown onion in butter. Add ketchup, vinegar, and brown sugar. Add all other ingredients to taste.
Place meatballs in crock pot and pour sauce over.
Cook 3 to 4 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Dip the chicken in the butter, then roll it in the cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until well done.

title: diabetic pound cake
directions: Pour water into a small saucepan; add raisins.
Cook until water is dissolved.
Mix applesauce, sweetener, eggs and oil. Stir until well blended.
Add other ingredients; stir well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: craft ornament dough
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Stir in water.
Knead for 5 minutes. Roll dough on floured surface until 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
If making hanging ornaments, make a small hole with a straw at top of ornament.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until edges turn brown, on well greased cookie sheets. Decorate with paints, glitter, glue, etc.
Use string or ribbon to hang.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix apples and eggs together.
Add sugar and oil; stir well. Mix dry ingredients together, then add to apple mixture.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Mix and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If too dry, add more mayonnaise. May be served hot or cold.

title: mexican rice
directions: Heat oil until very hot in a heavy pan.
Add rice; brown slightly, stirring constantly. Add garlic, onion, cumin, salt, tomato and broth or water. Bring to a boil. Reduce to low heat and cook 45 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Best if allowed to blend flavors in refrigerator overnight.

title: gelatin trifle
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Stir in strawberries and bananas.
Place cake cubes in large serving bowl; sprinkle with orange juice.
Spoon gelatin mixture over cake in bowl.
Chill 10 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Fry meat and onions until lightly browned.
Add other ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In
large bowl stir eggs, corn syrup, chocolate, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake
in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes or until knife comes out
clean	when inserted into pie.
Cook on wire rack.
Serves 8.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut buttered bread into strips.
Put in a greased casserole. Beat eggs slightly.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour over bread.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Bake casserole in a pan with a small amount of water in the pan.

title: party potatoes
directions: Beat potatoes and milk until smooth.
Grated Cheddar may be added as topping.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika (optional). Store overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until hot.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Bake approximately 20 minutes at 325°.
Good for breakfast or with just about any meal, especially fish.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together twice.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and flavoring. Mix well for good texture.
Bake layers 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet (crumbled like ground meat) and drain.
Combine celery, onions, bell pepper, soup mixture and rice with boiling water.
Do not drain.
Add sausage.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter. Mix well with crushed pretzels and pour into 8 x 12-inch pan. Bake 1 minute at 350°; cool. Cream the cream cheese and sugar together. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour on top of cooled pretzel crust. Refrigerate for 30 minutes. Mix Jell-O and boiling water and stir until Jell-O is dissolved. Add frozen strawberries. Refrigerate until slightly jelled. Pour on top of cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate until firm. May top with additional Cool Whip and garnish with fresh berries, if desired.

title: crab soup
directions: Remove any shells from crabmeat.
In top of double boiler or microwave, melt butter.
Add milk, parsley, celery, salt, pepper, Tabasco sauce and crabmeat.
Heat about 15 minutes but do not allow to boil.
Mix flour with little cold water to make paste, add to hot mixture and stir until it begins to thicken and add the cream and stir well.
Allow soup to simmer over hot water in double boiler for 20 minutes but do not allow to boil; stir occasionally.
Serve with saltines or Club crackers.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Put vanilla wafers
into bottom of cupcake papers.
Beat sugar, vanilla, eggs and cream cheese together until smooth.
Pour into papers.
Fill them 3/4 full.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes. Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Top with pie filling (cherry or blueberry). Makes 24.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and cook onion and garlic until soft. Add 1 cup water and remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed. Place on low heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
This works well for pork chops, spareribs and chicken.
Great for the grill.

title: pink passion dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: shrimp dip(hot or cold)
directions: Soften cream cheese with little mayonnaise; add ingredients. May be used in chafing dish or served cold.
Can also freeze.

title: sausage and escarole pasta
directions: Crumble sausage into large skillet.
Cook, breaking up with fork, until browned.
Remove from heat.
Spoon off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add oil, garlic and salt.
Stir until blended.
Add pepper and cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, slice about 1/2 inch off base of escarole.
Separate leaves and rinse well.
Stack and cut crosswise in 2-inch wide strips.
Increase heat to medium.
Add escarole in batches.
Cover pan.
As it wilts, add more until all has been added.
Cook, stirring once or twice, until escarole and pepper are tender.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter; add vanilla.
Gradually add confectioners sugar, one cup at a time, beating well.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often.
When all sugar is mixed in, icing will appear dry.
Add milk and beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
Keep icing covered with a damp cloth until ready to use.

title: chicken and bouillon
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water; set aside.
Wash and skin chicken.
Place in baking dish.
Add quartered potatoes and carrots.
Pour dissolved bouillon over chicken, potatoes and carrots.
Add diced onion.
Season to taste.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Can be cooked in microwave for 30 minutes on Full power.
Baste occasionally.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Layer potatoes and onion with 1/2 cup cheese and undiluted soup.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet and sour asparagus
directions: Pour boiled ingredients over asparagus.
Bring to boil and refrigerate overnight.
Take out cloves before serving.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat butter and cheese together until light and fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Good on carrot cake or apple cake.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook until peanuts stop popping.
Add soda.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet while still foaming.
Cool; break into desired pieces.

title: all kinds of fruit salad
directions: Cook pineapple juice, mustard and egg yolks.
Boil until thick and add marshmallows.
Pour over and drain fruit.
Let set overnight.
Add beaten whipped cream and bananas.
Top with a few cherries and serve.
Especially good at holiday dinners.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: hello dolly's
directions: Melt butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Make a crust by patting this mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, pecans and coconut.
Drizzle milk over top.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 30 minutes until golden brown on top.

title: grammie's lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream the butter or margarine and sugar; add flour to egg yolks and lemon juice.
Add milk gradually and fold in egg whites.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 30 minutes at 325°.

title: snow ball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 5 tablespoons water.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple, sugar and lemon juice.
Mix well. Refrigerate until thick.
Whip 4 packages whipped topping.
Break cake into bite-sized pieces.
Add cake to topping.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Add to refrigerated mixture.
Mix.
Transfer to buttered tube pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Whip remaining topping.
Ice cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: cheese cake
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with rolls.
In large bowl, beat sour cream, cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour on rolls. Sprinkle with cinnamon and raisins.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes in 325° oven.

title: black russian kahlua cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Pour into Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes, then remove from pan and pierce top of cake.
While warm, pour glaze over top.
Let cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cranberry stuffing balls
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage, celery and onions until sausage is done and vegetables are tender.
Drain excess fat.
In a large mixing bowl, combine meat mixture and remaining ingredients and enough broth to hold mixture together.
Shape into 8 to 10 balls. Place in a shallow greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Add noodles and cook for 15 minutes.
Add broccoli, Velveeta cheese, and milk.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Let set 1 hour.

title: rotel roast
directions: Place all ingredients in slow cooker.
Cook 8 to 12 hours on low heat.

title: beenie weenies
directions: Mix all ingredients in large casserole dish.
Bake at 325° until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: snicker brownies
directions: In double boiler, melt caramels with 1/3 cup of condensed milk over hot water; set aside and keep warm.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, margarine, nuts and remaining 1/3 cup condensed milk. Stir thoroughly until mixture is well combined and crumbly.
Press 1/2 of dough evenly into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces over baked dough; spread with caramel mixture, working quickly with broad spatula.
Crumble remaining dough and press lightly with spoon.
Return to oven and bake at 350° for 14 to 18 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 30 minutes, then refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients together and roll into tiny balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Mash out with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Be careful; they overbrown easily!

title: sausage squares
directions: Press 1 package crescent rolls in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Seal perforations. Mix cooked sausage and softened cream cheese. Spread on crescent rolls. Press remaining package of crescent rolls on top. Seal edges. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: chicken hmmm
directions: Sprinkle chicken with parsley and garlic salt.
Roll up and secure with a toothpick.
Roll in butter, then stuffing mix. Place in a heavily greased baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over chicken and moisten lightly with water.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: diabetic green bean salad
directions: Wash and trim beans.
Boil in small amounts of water until crisp and tender; drain.
Combine beans, tomato halves and onion; set aside.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Toss beans with yogurt dressing.
Chill several hours before serving.
Yields about 4 cups.

title: spud delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle potatoes with salt.
In a separate bowl, combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and garlic salt.
Fold into potatoes.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli potato soup rcb(serves 4 people)
directions: Cook potatoes, broccoli and onion in water for 1/2 hour or until just tender.
Add soup, seasonings, milk and butter.
Just before serving the piping hot mixture, add cheese and stir to melt.
If mixture is too thin, thicken slightly with the instant potato flakes.
Serve with crusty bread and a crispy salad for a hearty meal.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Pour jello in a saucepan and add water and marshmallows, then melt.
Add juice from the can of crushed pineapple, then place in refrigerator and cool.
After cooling, add pineapple, cottage cheese, pecans and Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator and cool.

title: no-cook peanutty fudge
directions: Chop
peanuts
finely.
Beat
peanut butter, margarine, corn syrup and vanilla.
Sift powdered sugar;
gradually beat in half of
sugar
and
all of cocoa.
Stir in rest of sugar; knead on wooden
board
until
well
blended and smooth.
Add peanuts. Press
in candy mold and unmold using a toothpick to loosen.
Or pat into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: scrambled cheese eggs
directions: Blend toasted onion dip mix with milk.
Add eggs and whip with a fork.
Crumble the cream cheese and sprinkle over the egg mixture.
Melt butter in a 9-inch skillet, making sure to coat the bottom and sides thoroughly.
Pour egg mixture into the hot skillet.
Reduce heat and cook slowly, gently lifting mixture from bottom and sides of skillet, allowing liquid to flow to bottom. Cook until set, but still moist.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bourbon dogs
directions: Combine ingredients and heat for 25 minutes in saucepan or 300° oven.
Makes approximately 50 appetizers.

title: wacky cake
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch cake pan. Sift dry ingredients into pan. Add remaining ingredients and mix with a fork. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Put the first 7 ingredients into a large bowl and beat together until smooth.
Pare and slice apples.
Pour 1/2 the batter in a greased tube pan, then 1/2 the apple slices, sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top.
Repeat with the other 1/2 of batter, apples, cinnamon, and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until it tests done.

title: crab dip(club member: keisha hudson)
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix all ingredients in bowl. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: mocha
directions: Blend on high.
Mix 2 tablespoons or to taste in boiling water.

title: round steak italiano(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Cut steak into 5 or 6 serving size pieces. Coat with salt, oregano and pepper. In slow-cooking pot, put in meat and onions, then pour spaghetti sauce over the meat. Cover and cook on LOW for 7 to 9 hours or until meat is tender. Turn the control on HIGH for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: southern rice pudding
directions: Mix together and spoon into serving dishes.
Add a dab of whipping cream to top along with red cherry.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add all ingredients.
Place in casserole. Top with crumbled Ritz crackers and butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.
Will serve 12 people.

title: milky way freezer ice cream
directions: Cut candy bars into bite size pieces.
Add Eagle Brand milk to candy and microwave until melted.
Remove from microwave and add Hershey's syrup.
Pour mixture into ice cream freezer. Afterwards, finish filling container with regular homogenized milk.
Freeze.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, eggplant, salt and cheese.
Cover with crackers and butter.
First of all, peel eggplant and cut into about 1-inch squares.
Cook 3 minutes and drain.
Put mixture in large casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
To spice up a day, just take a minute and put a dish of loving in it.

title: chocolate bar cookies
directions: Mix flour, butter and brown sugar until smooth.
Then spread in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Melt chocolate; spread on bar mixture.
Sprinkle on nuts.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in thin strips.
Brown meat.
Add seasonings, then add soup, broth and onion.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes until thickened, then add sour cream.

title: kraft bars
directions: Melt Kraft caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler.

title: chicken chimmingas
directions: Boil chicken with salt.
Chop into bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Chop green onions and bell peppers; saute in butter or Pam.
Add picante sauce, then chicken; heat.
Add cumin and let sit.
Spread flour tortillas with melted butter.
Fill with chicken mixture.
Add cheese.
Roll and heat in a 350° oven.

title: herb ball
directions: Mix and chill overnight.

title: amazin raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 9-inch round pans.
In a large bowl mix the first 10 ingredients on low with a mixer for two minutes.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.
Frost with 2 c. whipped cream.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes 5 minutes in salt water.
Drain.
Set overnight in sauce made with remaining ingredients.
Cook covered in oven at low temperature for 1 hour before serving.

title: tortilla flats
directions: Butter and brown both sides of the tortilla in a nonstick skillet.
Cover half of the tortilla as it lays in the skillet with cheese and hot sauce.
Let melt over low heat.
Fold over into half-moon shape and flip several times, making sure cheese is heated through and tortilla does not burn.

title: grape-nuts bread
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Lightly beat egg; stir in other liquids.
Add liquids to dry ingredients.
In greased bread pan, bake 1 hour or 40 minutes for 2 small loaves.

title: lemonade
directions: In a 1 gallon container, pour in Kool-Aid and sugar with some hot water.
Dissolve sugar and then pour in thawed frozen lemonade and fill container with water until full.

title: ground beef fillets
directions: Combine and blend first 9 ingredients in a bowl.
Stir in ground beef.
Shape into 6 fillets.
Wrap 1 slice bacon around each, securing with a toothpick.
Broil 10 minutes.
Turn; broil 8 minutes longer or grill on barbecue pit.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 400° until barely brown.

title: salmon (or tuna) loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in a well-greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mama barringer's pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Pour into pie shell. Cook on low heat until middle is firm. Makes 1 deep dish pie.

title: broccoli and cauliflower gratin
directions: Arrange florets in steamer basket over boiling water. Cover and steam 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain well. Arrange florets in greased 2-quart baking dish. Stir mayonnaise and next 5 ingredients. Spoon over florets. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cubed steak with red wine
directions: Saute the cubed steak in a large frying pan in about 1 to 2 tablespoons of butter over medium heat for about 3 minutes on each side.
Remove cubed steak and reserve remaining melted butter in a pan; saute mushrooms until brown.
Sprinkle flour over mushrooms and butter and blend in.
Add wine and beef stock and cook until mixture comes to a boil.
Add cubed steak and juices in dish.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, gelatin and seasoning in a large bowl. Add celery and shrimp and blend well. Pour into a greased mold (1 1/2-quart) and chill for several hours. Serve with Waverly Wafers. May be frozen.

title: moist and tender chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt in medium bowl. Beat sugar, butter and vanilla in large mixer bowl until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Alternately beat flour mixture and water into creamed mixture until well blended.
Spread into two well-greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cheesy-potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except the corn flakes and butter in a large bowl. Grease a large casserole dish; add mixture.
Add the corn flakes and melted butter; mix, then add to the top of mixture. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add all other ingredients gradually until all are mixed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done (check with toothpick).
Makes 2 large or 3 small layers.

title: linguine with shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Bring water with salt to a boil for pasta.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat and add the garlic and chopped red and green peppers.
Add tomatoes and cook 10 minutes.
Add oregano, salt and pepper.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Mix until frothy or consistency you prefer.
Enjoy.

title: corncakes
directions: Place corn meal and water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs and milk together and add to corn meal mixture.
Combine salt, baking powder and flour. Add to first mixture and stir until blended. Heat skillet or griddle with about 3 tablespoons of oil.
Spoon mixture into
hot oil, approximately 2 to 3 tablespoons per cake.
Brown on both sides.
More oil may be added as needed or desired.
If batter is too thin, add more flour.
If too thick, add more milk.
Serve with apple butter, syrup (like Karo) or honey.

title: apricot bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; stir in rolled oats and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of the crumb mixture into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Spread with preserves. Cover the preserves with the remaining crumb mixture.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) about 35 minutes or until browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: coffee for 30
directions: This recipe for a 30-cup coffee maker is easy to remember and can be easily portioned for smaller amounts.

title: hearty minestrone
directions: Bring to a boil the broth, water and tomatoes.
Add vegetables, beans, cabbage, oregano, salt and pepper.
Return to boil and cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: marinade for pot roast
directions: Combine all ingredients in container large enough to hold both marinade and pot roast.
After marinade ingredients have been mixed, add meat, coating on all sides.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours, turning occasionally.

title: bloody mary brunch mix
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and reserve; mix with vodka and serve over ice.

title: mock shepherd's pie
directions: Brown onion in skillet in small amount of hot fat.
Add beef, salt and pepper.
Cook until browned.
Drain beans; add to beef mixture with soup.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Add flour to form a ball that you can pick up.
Roll out thin. Cut into strips and cook until tender.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons of sugar, 1 stick oleo (melted) and graham cracker crumbs.
Line a 9 x 12-inch pan with this.
Combine 2 sticks of oleo, extract and powdered sugar.
Beat with electric mixer for about 15 minutes on medium speed.
Pour over crumbs. Layer remaining ingredients, in order listed, over filling. Garnish top with extra strawberries.
Refrigerate for several hours before cutting.

title: turkey scallopini with sherried cream
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add finely diced onions and turkey cutlets.
Brown cutlets on both sides and remove.
Add sherry and let thicken, stirring constantly.
Slice mushrooms and add.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add heavy cream as a final.
Serve over turkey cutlets.

title: ellie's buttermilk yeast biscuits
directions: Scald buttermilk; let cool.
Add sugar, salt and shortening. Add soda and yeast water (dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water). Add 1/2 cup flour to this mixture and beat well.
Add remaining flour and mix.
Let rise 90 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Put in bowl sugar and flour.
Mix in saucepan Coca-Cola, butter, oil and cocoa.
Let mixture come to a boil.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Stir well, then add to dry ingredients.
Mix well and add buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Put in large pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Stir in chili seasoning.
In 13 x 9-inch glass dish layer beef, chili hot beans and Mexicorn.
Fix yellow rice according to package directions. When finished, stir in tomatoes and soup.
Put this mixture on top of Mexicorn.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
About 10 minutes before done, sprinkle cheese on top and finish baking.
For a spicy dish, use 1 can Ro-Tel tomatoes instead of plain tomatoes.

title: one pan toffee bars
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg yolk with fork in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stir in baking
mix until moistened, mix will be crumbly.
Press mixture evenly in pan.
Bake until light and brown, about 16 to 18 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Let stand until chips are softened. Spread evenly over top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into bars.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked 10-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: green beans amandine
directions: Cut green beans French-style (slice in half from end to end). Cook, covered, in a small amount of boiling salted water for 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Add salt and pepper to taste and mash.
Combine soup, pimento, carrots, onion and sour cream.
Add to squash.
Pour melted butter over bread crumbs.
Alter layers of squash mixture and bread crumbs, ending with bread crumbs on top. Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.
It should be bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine other ingredients except bread crumbs.
Add broccoli.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 40 minutes in 400° oven.

title: chocolate velvet cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, nuts, 3 tablespoons granulated sugar and margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and brown sugar, mixing at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Blend in chocolate, milk, and vanilla extract; pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Combine sour cream and 2 tablespoons granulated sugar; carefully spread over cheesecake.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill.
Garnish with mint candies.

title: coffee can bread
directions: You will need two 1-pound coffee cans.

title: beef-barley soup
directions: Heat oil and beef; cook, stirring often, until brown.
Add 8 cups of water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is fork-tender.
With slotted spoon, remove meat.
With 2 forks, shred meat.
Set aside.
In cup, dissolve bouillon in 1/2 cup of water.
Add to soup kettle the tomatoes, carrots, onion, celery, barley, salt and pepper.
Stir in meat. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until vegetables are tender.

title: heavenly rice dessert
directions: Cook rice.
Rinse and drain well, let stand and cool.
Put in maraschino cherries which have been drained and cut in half.
Add sugar to taste.
Add vanilla.
Add pineapple, drained, and marshmallows (tiny colored ones gives it a lot of color).
Add Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Place in mold and chill well before serving.

title: mock apple butter
directions: Peel and seed zucchini; chop coarsely.
Put zucchini in blender with vinegar; blend until smooth.
Pour in saucepan with remaining ingredients and cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches desired thickness.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chicken acapulco
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Stir in the next 9 ingredients, mixing well.

Spoon about 1/2 cup chicken mixture in center of each tortilla; roll up and place, seam side down, in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over tortillas.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yield:
5 servings.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat salad oil and add rice.
Stir until brown.
Add onion, celery, pepper and mushrooms and cook for approximately 5 minutes with rice.
Add tomatoes, can of water and salt; cook, covered, until all water is absorbed and rice is soft.
Serve hot.

title: oriental turkey-orange skillet
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in a skillet.
Cover and cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and cook 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients; set aside.
Then mix other ingredients.
Mix both together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut out middle of a double round marble rye pumpernickel.
Break middle into pieces.
Also break a loaf of one rye and one pumpernickel, unsliced.
Fill middle with dip and serve with pieces of bread.

title: dirt cake
directions: Freeze cookies overnight.
Chop cookies in a blender until they look like soil.
Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Fold Cool Whip into this mixture.
Layer soil and cream mixture in a large bowl or large clean flowerpot.
For added flair, place plastic flowers and a gummy worm on top.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way bars with a small amount of milk in the microwave or in a double boiler.
Mix melted candy bars, sugar, margarine and eggs together.
In separate bowl, combine baking soda and buttermilk; set aside.
Alternate, adding buttermilk mixture and flour to candy mixture until all is used.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into 3 eight-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa and soda.
Mix together water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Mix all together.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes; cut into wedges.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake, a few at a time, coating the potatoes with the cheese mixture.
Melt butter and place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place potatoes in a layer.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning once during baking. When golden, sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Melt oleo or butter in flour.
Add broth and milk to make a thin white sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Layer crumbs, chicken and sauce, as many layers as pan will hold.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake until bubbly and crumbs are browned.
Bake at 400° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cottage cheese-deviled eggs
directions: Halve eggs and remove yolks.
In a blender, combine and blend until smooth all remaining ingredients.
Garnish with snipped parsley, if desired.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, mayonnaise, cheese, onion and soup. Mix well. Pour into baking dish. Combine cracker crumbs with melted margarine and spread on top of vegetables. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Bring water to boiling in a saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add tea bags.
Cover and steep 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Stir in spices and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Simmer 1 minute longer.
Add juices.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: summer fruit and cheese salad
directions: Combine all ingredients gently and serve very cold on greens. Makes 2 servings.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: In frypan put garlic and butter until garlic is browned.
Add flour and chicken broth about a minute until pasty.
Add heavy cream, cheese, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until thick (bring to boil).
Cook broccoli as package directs.
Put broccoli in pan.
Lay chicken over broccoli and then add cream sauce.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: coney dog sauce
directions: Mix hamburger and hot water together in crock pot;
stir till meat is broken up.
Add other ingredients.
Cook on LOW, without lid, for 4 to 6 hours, stirring occasionally.
Freezes well.

title: coconut pecan square cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Mix the margarine, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup flour in a bowl until crumbly.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Layer cucumbers, salt and onions in a large container.
Cover with ice cubes.
Let sit for 3 hours.
Drain.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per package directions.
Mix all ingredients and place
in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in stick of butter or margarine.
Put in casserole.
Add rice and beef broth.
Cover and bake at 350° and stir occasionally, about 1 hour.

title: mushroom toss salad
directions: Prepare Italian dressing as directed & add sugar.
Pour on artichoke hearts, olives, mushrooms, & onions -- cover & refrigerate over night to marinate (no more than 24 hrs).
Place greens in large plastic bag with paper towel.
After washing-close bag & refrigerate up to 24 hrs. 5 minutes before serving take out the paper towels from the greens bag, add marinated mixture to greens, close bag tightly & shake to coat greens.
Put in bowl & sprinkle with parmesan cheese if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage cook and drain. Grease 13 x 9 x 3 pan and line with rolls. Sprinkle sausage and cheese. Combine remaining ingredients and beat well. Pour over sausage. Bake 15 minutes at 425° or 30 minutes if cold.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Mix and spread on quartered English muffins.
Freeze for at least 30 minutes, or several weeks.

title: icee punch
directions: Mix ingredients and freeze.
Remove from freezer about an hour before serving.
Pour 1 or 2 large bottles of ginger ale over this before serving.

title: easy gingersnaps
directions: Combine shortening and sugars. Add egg.

Beat until fluffy. Add molasses and beat well. Sift dry ingredients together and add. Chill dough. Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar. Place 2-inches apart on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: no cook basil, walnut and garlic sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in small bowl.
Stir to blend.
Toss with hot pasta.
Serve at once.

title: erma's frosting
directions: Put all together and beat until creamy.

title: spaghetti marinara
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
Drain liquid from tomatoes.
Reserve liquid.
Chop tomatoes; add to garlic, blending well.
Add liquid from tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Bring mixture to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer slowly 1 hour.
Add parsley and olives.
Continue cooking about 5 minutes longer.

title: cucumber cocktail sandwiches
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise	and
salad dressing mix.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Spread on thin slices of party rye.
Top with thin slice of cucumber.
Sprinkle
with
dill weed.
Cover and chill.	Can be made 24 hours ahead.

title: florentine layers
directions: Cook sausage, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Stir in sauce and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix the two soups and rotel tomatoes together and heat thoroughly.
Cube the chicken.
Layer in a casserole dish-soup-chips-chicken soup and cheese.
Put in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt. Gradually add milk.
Mix well.
Add beaten egg yolks. Cook over hot water in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thick and creamy. Add peanut butter and mashed sweet potatoes.
Mix well. Cool slightly.
Pour into prebaked 9-inch pie crust. Top with meringue and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Fold all ingredients together and put in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for
45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine vinegar, jam, brown sugar, Worcestershire and catsup. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cornstarch and cook until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken and cook until meat is done.

title: jumbo chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine, sugars and egg thoroughly.

Stir in flour, soda and salt (dough will be stiff). Stir in nuts and chocolate chips. Drop dough by 1/4 cup about 3-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until edges are set, 12 to 15 minutes.
(Centers will be soft.)
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: chili mac bake
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Stir in green pepper. Spoon half of dinner into 1-quart casserole.
Top with chili and remaining dinner; cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: almond fluff cookies
directions: Beat with mixer for 15 minutes, until stiff (not gooey). Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Add 2 large tomatoes without the seeds and toss. Season with salt
and
pepper;	chill
about 4 to 6 hours.
I usually blanch the
broccoli
and	carrots about 3 minutes.
Let them cool. Don't
cook
broccoli
and	carrots together; cook them separate.

title: crabmeat dip no. 2
directions: Mix all together night before.
Use with chips or crackers.

title: speared shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add chili sauce.
Add next several ingredients and process until smooth.
Set aside.
Loosely thread shrimp on 6 (12-inch) skewers.
Place kabobs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon mixture over kabobs.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator 1 hour.
Remove kabobs from marinade.
Grill over hot coals 3 minutes on each side until shrimp turns pink.
To serve, squeeze lemon wedges over grilled shrimp.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: no bake fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Melt marshmallows in Eagle Brand milk in double boiler.
Pour melted mixture into other ingredients and mix well.
Divide into 4 balls.
Roll into jelly rolls. Chill overnight in waxed paper.
Cut into slices to serve.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Bring butterscotch topping to boil in a small sauce pan, stirring constantly. Pour into pie shell. Arrange pecans on top; chill. Prepare pudding with milk as directed on package. Pour into pie shell; place plastic wrap on surface of filling. Chill 1 1/2 hours. Remove plastic wrap. Cover with cool whip. Makes 8 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Drain corn and tomatoes and save juice.
Brown beef and add all other ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until cooked through (set).

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Slice strawberries into baked pie shell.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, water and salt in saucepan.
Cook and boil 2 minutes until clear.
Take from stove; add package of jello and few drops of red food coloring.
Pour while still hot over strawberries. Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: mailman's baked beans
directions: Drain sausage and bacon.
Combine all ingredients and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Makes a lot.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken and cut into large chunks.
Mix mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice together.
Add all ingredients and toss until thoroughly mixed.
Let marinate overnight.
If serving individually, serve in lettuce cups and garnish with pineapple chunks and avocado slices.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together.
Drain well and add soup and 1 can of hot enchilada sauce.
Heat up until well blended. Soak flour tortilla shells in 1 can of enchilada sauce.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and butter to boiling point in heavy saucepan. Dump in salt and flour all at once.
Lower heat; stir rapidly.
As mixture thickens and leaves sides of pan, stir into definite ball-like mass.
Remove from heat.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating hard after each addition, until dough becomes light and fluffy.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Makes 6 large puffs or about 15 small ones.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake for 25 minutes.

title: deviled ham ball
directions: Thoroughly mix ham and cheese.
Add all remaining ingredients (except nuts and parsley); stir.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Shape into balls.
Roll balls in mixture of nuts and parsley.

title: easy oil buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add oil, salt and sugar.
Put flour in this mixture and knead.
Cover bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Make into buns.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: browned rice(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Melt butter or oleo in skillet.
Add rice.
Saute until rice is brown, being careful not to burn.
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat; add beef consomme and onion (sliced thin).
Bake in 350° oven until all juice is absorbed (approximately 1 hour). Great with ham, steak or chicken.

title: easy beef tortilla pizzas
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a large skillet over medium-high heat until beef is no longer pink.
Pour off drippings.
Sprinkle oregano and salt over beef, stirring to combine.
Place tortillas on 2 large baking sheets.
Lightly brush surface of each tortilla with oil.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 3 minutes.
Divide beef mixture evenly over tops or tortillas; divide tomato and desired topping over beef mixture.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes, rearranging baking sheets halfway through cooking time.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage, fry and drain.
Set aside.
In 9 x 12-inch baking dish, layer half the sausage, 2 slices bread (broken in pieces) and 1/2 cup cheese.
Repeat the layers.
In bowl, beat the eggs, salt, pepper, dry mustard and milk. Pour over layers in baking dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oleo over low heat until melted.
Blend flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Stir in chicken and frozen vegetables.
Use Celery Seed Pastry.

title: kielbasa appetizer(great for parties!)
directions: Boil kielbasa for 1/2 an hour, then slice thin.
Mix together vinegar, brown sugar and dry mustard and heat thoroughly.
Add kielbasa to sauce mixture.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix dressing
and
shrimp.
Add lemon juice and Tabasco sauce. Cover
and chill overnight.
Serve with chips, crackers or raw veggies.

title: chinese noodle candy
directions: Melt first 2 ingredients over slow fire in double boiler.
Add noodles and cashews.
Drop on waxed paper and cool.

title: beef jerky
directions: Meat strips need to be cut the length of the roast while still frozen.

title: spiced cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form in 1-inch balls.
Saute in 2 tablespoons butter.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Heat butter, syrup and chocolate chips to boiling in 3-quart pan; stir constantly. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large mixing bowl.
Toss quickly until completely covered with chocolate.
Fold in marshmallows, 1 cup at a time.
Press mixture into pan with the back of a buttered spoon.
Let stand until firm, about 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: ham and cheese stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; pat dry.
Rub each potato with shortening and prick several places with fork.
Bake for 1 hour or until done. Cut potatoes lengthwise; scoop out inside, leaving a thin shell.

title: peppercorn chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken between plastic wrap.
Pound chicken with mallet.
Sprinkle with peppercorn.
Heat a nonstick skillet.
Melt butter and add chicken.
Cook, turning once, until chicken is done, about 5 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken and keep warm.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Have everything at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar. Add flavorings.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder together and set aside.
Mix milk and sour cream together. Add flour mixture alternating with milk mixture to creamed batter. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: snookie's homemade potato salad
directions: Cook and peel potatoes.
Peel hard-boiled eggs.
Dice potatoes and eggs into small, bite size pieces.
Chop celery and onion into very small pieces.
Combine all of the ingredients used so far into a large mixing bowl.
Add vinegar.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve chilled.

title: date loaf
directions: Combine the creamed butter, honey and spices.
Add beaten eggs. Sift the salt, soda and flour together and add with applesauce to previous mixture.
Mix a small amount of flour with dates, raisins and nuts to coat.
Add them to the batter.
Mix well and place in greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Melt butter and pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until thick.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into four pieces each.
Combine 2/3 cup white sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Mix biscuits in mixture.
Place 1/2 in Bundt pan (greased).

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Layer chicken in a shallow pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn once or twice while baking.

title: angel buns from bisquick
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in the warm water in a medium mixing bowl.
Mix in the baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Smooth into a ball on breadboard dusted with baking mix.
Knead at least 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut with a biscuit cutter dipped in baking mix.
Put on an ungreased cookie sheet and let rise in a warm place for about 30 minutes or doubled in size. Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes until golden brown. Yield:
9 to 12 buns.

title: double corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; save drippings.
Drain corn; save liquid.
Add water to liquid to make 1/2 cup.
Add to drippings.
Add onion, potatoes and salt; cover and simmer for 15 minutes, or until tender.
Add soup, milk, corn and cream of celery soup.
Heat through.
Crumble bacon over top with some pats of butter on top.

title: pink salad delight
directions: Mix together, but do not beat.
Chill before serving.
Serves 10.

title: praline squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat 1 cup oleo, 3/4 cup brown sugar and the granulated sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg yolk, vanilla and salt. Stir in 1/2 cup of the nuts, then the flour.
Press dough evenly into 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes .

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients slowly for 1 hour. Stir frequently. Add the butter and powdered sugar. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
You can add red food coloring to this if you want.

title: herbed cheese
directions: Thoroughly mix all together in blender and mold into any shape desired.
Cover and refrigerate at least overnight.

title: diet crunchy baked chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Brush chicken with milk.
Coat with cereal mixture.
Place on nonstick baking pan. Dot cutlets with 2 teaspoons low-fat margarine.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400° or until done.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and refrigerate 2 hours.
Drain and press out as much juice as possible, but do not reuse.
Mix the vinegar and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers.
Put in small freezer containers and freeze.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Combine 1/3 cup sugar with 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 cup crushed pineapple.
Cook until thick and clear.
Allow to cool. Combine cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour pineapple mixture into bottom of unbaked 9-inch pie shell; then add cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes; then turn oven temperature back to 325° and continue baking for approximately 55 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook, skin and debone chicken.
Cut into chunks.
Save broth. Mix soup and pepper.
Mix margarine, milk and flour in separate bowl.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Then pour flour mixture over all.
Bake for 30 minutes in 425° oven.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Boil rice according to directions on box and set aside.
Put margarine in pan.
Add celery and onion (both cut fine) and fry on low until tender.
Pour this into a small bowl.
Brown the pork chops in the pan for a few minutes.
Add margarine or butter, if necessary.
Put pork chops in a baking dish or can use a crock-pot.
Mix together rice, celery, onions and the mushroom soup.
Put this on top of the pork chops.
Cover later with foil if rice gets too brown.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
If using crock-pot, put on low for 2 to 3 hours.

title: peach pudding
directions: Cream sugar, peaches and soda.
Add salt, nuts and eggs; then beat.
Add flour and beat again.
Pour in a 9 x 9-inch pan (greased or sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: best ever spicy spaghetti
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in a large Dutch oven until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain; stir in next 12 ingredients.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaves; stir in Burgundy.
Spoon sauce over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Yields 8 to 10 servings. Freezes well.

title: new england rum pie
directions: Blend together in mixer until creamy the cream cheese, eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and 1 1/2 tablespoons dark rum. Pour into extra-serving size graham cracker Ready-Crust. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Edges will puff, center will be mostly set.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion in Dutch oven.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: graham cracker pecan pie
directions: Add baking powder and salt to egg whites; beat until foamy and begins to peak, not dry.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar; continue beating.
Add vanilla.
Fold in graham crackers, chopped pecans and remaining sugar.
Grease pie plate with butter and pour batter into it.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brown sugar pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, milk, vanilla, sugar and flour.
Beat well.
Add margarine, mixing well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese balls
directions: In a food processor combine Cheddar, American and cream cheese, buttermilk, Worcester sauce, hot pepper sauce and garlic powder.
Process until smooth.
Remove the mixture and pat into a ball.
Cover in plastic wrap, refrigerate 2 hours or until firm. Combine chilli and paprika on a plate.
Mix well.
Roll cheese balls in mixture until well coated.

title: french onion soup
directions: Place butter and onions in cooker.
Saute until onions are golden brown.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add all together. Cover and bring to a boil.
Switch to low.
Cook for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts until double in size.
Rub Parmesan into each side and pound it in well.
Dip chicken in egg whites and press into bread crumbs on both sides.
Saute 3 minutes per side in melted margarine in a nonstick skillet.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.
Has 290 calories, 6 g fat.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for butter and cheese crackers. Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix melted butter and crumbled crackers together.
Add to top of other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Lightly brown beef and onions; add taco mix and 3/4 cups water.
Mix well.
Add 2 heaping tablespoons of tomato paste, 1/2 jar of medium or hot picante sauce (if you use chunky picante sauce you may need to add a little water) and simmer until thick, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In bowl, mix remaining tomato paste, 1 jar medium or hot picante sauce and 1 jar mild picante sauce.
(Reserve the half jar of medium or hot for later.) Put enough tomato paste mixture in baking dish to slightly cover the bottom of dish.

Now you are ready to roll your enchiladas. Take 1 wrap at the rounded edge, place 1 heaping tablespoon meat mixture and 1 heaping tablespoon grated cheese; roll lightly and place seam side down in baking dish.
This will make 10.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients and press into bottom and up sides of 8-inch pie plate.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: overnight slaw
directions: Place alternate layers of the cabbage and onion in a bowl. Combine the sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed, mustard and oil in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over the cabbage mixture and cover airtight.
Refrigerate overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: twice-baked parmesan-chive potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pierce potatoes in several places with a fork.
Place on a baking sheet or oven rack.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes, until potatoes feel soft when squeezed.
Remove from oven and let cool 15 minutes.

title: easy-to-make spoon rolls
directions: Add yeast to water.
Melt margarine and cream with sugar in a large bowl.
Add egg and stir into mixture; then add dissolved yeast and mix well.
Add flour and stir until mixed well.
Place in airtight bowl and store in refrigerator.
To cook, spoon into well-greased muffin pans and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Dough can be kept 2 or 3 weeks in refrigerator if kept in bowl with airtight lid.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: apple crisp
directions: Add cinnamon on top of apples.
Add water.
Mix flour, sugar and oleo.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham 'n' cheese potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add onion and cook, stirring, until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended.
Gradually stir in milk and dry milk powder.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
In 2-quart greased casserole, layer half the potatoes, ham cubes and sauce.
Repeat layers and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake covered 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer, or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple dessert
directions: Place sliced apples in a 9 x 13 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Sprinkle jello over evenly.
Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Cut in butter until mix is crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Wilt cabbage leaves in hot water.
Mix thoroughly the ground beef, cooked rice, egg, salt, pepper and onion.
Roll all these ingredients in cabbage leaves.
Place in cooker or skillet.
Add can of tomatoes.
Cook over medium heat until cabbage is tender.

title: pecan swirl pudding cake
directions: Combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Blend.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour 2/3 of the batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with sugar-nut mixture.

title: cottage cheese mashed potatoes
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients to boiling, remove from heat.
Add minced onion and instant mashed potatoes.
Whip with fork.
Fold in cottage cheese, turn in 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oyster or shrimp spaghetti
directions: Saute onions and parsley in butter and olive oil.
After parsley and onions are soft, add garlic and pepper.
Do not simmer garlic too long; it will get bitter if overdone.
Add oysters or shrimp.
If shrimp is used, peel and devein.
Shrimp and oysters will be done in 5 to 10 minutes.
You can use 6 soft shell crabs. Crabs take about 20 to 30 minutes.
Have spaghetti drained and pour some juice over spaghetti to keep it from sticking together.

title: "our" sour cream
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth and creamy.
Makes 1 cup.

title: broccoli cauliflower casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, baking powder, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Gradually stir in flour.
Form balls with dough and chill 1 hour.
Roll out on floured dough board.
Use cookie cutters to form desired shapes.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cookies are best if removed from oven just before they begin to brown.
Decorate when cool with frosting as desired.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook onions and mushrooms until tender.
Add meat and cook until brown.
Mix soup, flour, salt and pepper to meat mixture. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Add sour milk and noodles.
Heat through and serve.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine lemonade concentrate and sweetened condensed milk. Mix into Cool Whip, stirring until well blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill.

title: peanut pie
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, shortening and salt.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Pour this hot syrup slowly over eggs, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add vanilla and peanuts.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 375°; bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.

title: kahlua chocolate cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake in Bundt pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Put sugar, corn syrup, water, butter and salt in a saucepan and cook, stirring, until the sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until syrup forms a brittle ball in cold water.
Add vanilla and stir only enough to mix it through the hot syrup.

Place the popped corn in a bowl large enough for mixing. Pour the cooked syrup slowly over the popped corn and mix well. Wet hands slightly and shape corn into balls using only enough pressure to make the balls stick together.

title: hawaiian summer salad
directions: Toss just before serving.
Very good for summer luncheons. Pretty if served in pineapple shells.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add other ingredients and mix. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 12-14.

title: chocolate log roll
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender; pour in 9 x 13-inch jelly roll pan with waxed paper sprayed with Pam.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In large cook pot saute onions, garlic and oil until tender. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, oregano, and pepper into pot. Simmer for 1 hour.
Optional, you can add meatballs, sausage or ground hamburger for meat sauce.

title: hot molasses punch
directions: Mix together ice and brandy.
Add champagne.
Makes 8 (12 ounce) servings.

title: christmas morning breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage, drain, add cheese, mix well.
Sprinkle
mixture in pie shell.
Beat eggs, add onions, peppers, and cream.
Pour in pie shell bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Serve. Garnish with red and bell peppers. Can be refrigerated overnight and baked the next morning. This is great for a quick breakfast on Christmas morning.

title: party cheese
directions: Mix cream cheese with salad dressing; add Parmesan cheese. Broil 10 to 12 slices of bacon to crisp.
Drain, cool and crumble very fine.
Add to cheese mixture.
Cut up fine 4 cups spring garden onions and 1/4 bell pepper.
Blend peppers and onions with cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Pound the cutlets to tenderize, then sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dip in flour, then pat off excess.
Dip first in beaten eggs, coating thoroughly then in bread crumbs.
Pat crumbs well into cutlets.
Chill coated cutlets for an hour or so if possible. The chilling will help the crumb coating adhere to the meat. In an electric skillet heated to 300°, pour salad oil to a depth of 1/4 inch.
Saute cutlets until light brown.
Then place them in a greased shallow casserole.
Place sliced Mozzarella cheese over the cutlets.
In a small saucepan, combine tomato sauce and oregano. Bring to a boil and pour over cutlets.
Sprinkle heavily with grated cheese, then with paprika and salad oil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until Parmesan browns.

title: southwest soup
directions: Mix all ingredients; do not drain. Cook slow about 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: frito salad
directions: Mix beans, cheese, onions and salad dressing together.
Chill. Just before serving, add remaining ingredients.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix; pour over cooled cheese mixture.
Add remaining Cool Whip for topping.
Refrigerate.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook until slightly thick.
Pour over layers of bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: spinach pie(this is great with italian dishes)
directions: Thaw spinach and drain.
Cook rice.
Mix grated cheese, onions, eggs (beaten) and olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients (rice last because it will still be hot).
Mix well.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Add top pie crust.
Bake at 350° to 375° until crust is golden brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar, Karo syrup, butter flavor, margarine and salt together for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Pour over corn.
Place in shallow pan.
Place in oven preheated to 250°.
Turn oven off and stir occasionally.
After cooling, store in airtight container.

title: light rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add other ingredients.
Knead. Roll, cut and place in greased dish.
Rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° until done.
Makes 20 rolls.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring sugar, oil, wine vinegar, pepper and salt to a boil.
Let cool.
In colander, drain peas, corn, green beans and pimento.
Add celery, onion and green pepper.
You can add other vegetables, if you wish.
I added some carrots and cucumbers.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients with the mashed potatoes.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 to 1 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hoagie sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shake well.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken-in-a-sack
directions: Grease inside of a paper bag.
Dip chicken in barbecue sauce and place in bag.
Bake at 325° until tender.
Remove from bag, baste with more barbecue sauce and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes in open pan.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Let set until thick and syrupy. Thin salad dressing with milk.
Mix it and the onions, cottage cheese and carrots into the jello.
Pour into mold and let set until solid.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over heat. Add flour, salt and pepper. Cook for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in milk. Return to heat and cook until thick and bubbly, stirring often. Mix with other ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients,
drop
by teaspoonful into hot oil and cook until brown about 6 minutes.

title: charlie's cornbread
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Add all the other ingredients and blend together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: buffalo pretzels
directions: Break up pretzels onto a large cookie sheet.
Mix oil and dressing; pour over pretzels.
Sprinkle liberally with dill weed and lemon pepper.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir at 15 minute intervals.

title: fruit cake
directions: Melt butter in hot coffee and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients. Add nuts and fruit, stirring after each addition.
By now, coffee should be warm.
Break eggs into it, stirring.
Add to the dry ingredients.
Stir in the preserves.
Pour (or throw) mix into well-greased pans.
Bake at 350°, time varies by pan.
Loaf pans take about 1 1/2 hours.
Use a toothpick to check, or bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Place a pan 1/2 full of water in the oven while baking.
Makes 4 to 6 cakes, depending on the size of the pans.

title: cranberry juice
directions: Cook cranberries and water until all skins pop.
Strain through cheesecloth or screened colander.
Heat and add sugar and boil for two minutes. Chill before serving.
If too thick add more water.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In a large pan, melt margarine.
Add garlic and tomato sauce. Add chicken.
Simmer over low heat approximately 1 hour until chicken breaks apart easily with a fork.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; fold in crabmeat and crumbs. Let stand for 3 minutes. Shape into patties and place on waxed paper-lined baking sheet. Cover and chill at least 1 hour. Saute crab cakes in olive oil in a large nonstick skillet, 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until golden. Place on paper towels to drain.

title: silver cake
directions: Cream
shortening.
Add sugar gradually and keep creaming.
(I do
this
by hand until it is light and fluffy, like whipped cream.
This
is my secret of a fine-textured velvet-like
cake.) Sift
flour, baking powder and soda three times, then
add alternately
with
buttermilk
and flavoring to the creamed mixture.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn into
3 greased and floured cake pans and bake at 350° until a pick inserted
into
the
center comes out clean.
Frost with Silver Cake Icing.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl or pot, adding only enough bread crumbs to hold mixture together.
(Don't want mix to be too dry.)
Shape into meatballs.
Brown in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels, then add to simmering Italian sauce (recipe in sauce section).
Skim off any fat that forms on sauce with spoon.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Rinse and drain broccoli.
Chop to measure 2 cups, both florets and stalks (optional).
Grate cheese and slice scallions (thin). Regular onions may be used.
In bowl beat eggs with broth, cream, salt and pepper sauce.
Prick bottom and sides of pie shell.
Bake in 450° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle 1/2 grated Parmesan over bottom of pie shell.
Scatter 1/2 broccoli, 1/2 Swiss cheese and 1/2 scallions.
Repeat with remaining.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Sprinkle other 1/2 grated cheese.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Lower temperature to 325°.
Bake 25 minutes, until set.
Knife will come out clean.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding and eggs in a large mixer bowl; beat until well blended.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle sugar, butterscotch chips and nuts over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: To make 1 cup hot chocolate, mix 1/3 cup mix to a cup of boiling water.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, oil and vinegar.
Mix well.
Sift in flour and soda.
Add milk slowly.
Add flavoring and red food coloring.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and chopped onion in boiling, salted water until done.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream; stir in shredded carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onion.

title: 3 step cheesecake
directions: Step 1:
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer until blended.
Add eggs and mix.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco well.
Add eggs, margarine, flour, milk and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: tuna ring
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased baking dish in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Serve with Cheese Sauce.

title: grandma's chicken casserole
directions: In large bowl, mix soup, chicken, milk, celery, salt, mayonnaise and pimento.
Add dry noodles and sprinkle cheese over top.
Pour mixture into 13 x 9-inch greased pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: orange jello delight
directions: Add 3 c. boiling water to jello; mix well.
Add frozen orange juice concentrate and drained pineapple and mandarins.
Mix and refrigerate until set.
Mix (dry) pudding with cool whip and spread on top of set jello.
Sprinkle with grated cheddar cheese.

title: spuds 'n onions
directions: Before grilling:
Peel potatoes (if desired) and cut into 4 to 5 crosswise slices.
Place 1 onion slice between each potato slice and reassemble potato.
Secure slices with toothpick or skewer. Drizzle melted margarine and sprinkle salt, pepper and paprika over potatoes.
Place each potato on large square of heavy-duty foil; seal securely.

title: double chocolate gooey butter cake
directions: Preheat oven 350°. Lightly grease

13x9 pan. Combine cake mix, 1 egg, 1 stick butter, melted and stir until well blended. Pat mixture into pan. Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add the remaining 2 eggs and the cocoa and powdered sugar. Continue beating until well mixed. Slowly add remaining stick butter and the vanilla. Stir in nuts. Spread over cake mixture in pan. Bake 40-50 minutes the center should be a little gooey when finished baking.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and let stand 15 minutes or while pastry is being made.
Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry rolled 1/8-inch thick.
Fill with rhubarb mixture.
Adjust top crust and moisten edge of pastry with cold water.
Press edges together. Trim off excess pastry.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes and 350° for 30 minutes or longer.

title: peachy chicken
directions: Combine the jam, water and lemon juice to make the marinade sauce.
Marinate the chicken in the marinade sauce overnight. Bake at 350°, occasionally basting with the extra marinade sauce.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl.
(Reserve 1/4 cup beef for top of cheese ball.)
Mix well.
Divide into two balls.
Top with reserved chopped beef.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: blueberry cupcake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add blueberries and pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix.
Make into walnut sized balls and place in baking pan.

title: lo-cal clam sauce for pasta
directions: Combine all ingredients in small saucepan.
Heat to simmering. Serve over spaghetti.
Makes 2/3 cup.
Contains 75 calories per 1/3 cup serving.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Prepare cake mix, following directions on box.
Pour half of batter into pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all in a large bowl and mix well with hands.
Wash hands, preheat oven to 350° and grease 8 to 9-inch square pan. Add meat mixture and spread evenly in pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain any grease off after removing from oven.

title: pound cake
directions: *To get 1 pound of flour, empty the powdered sugar in a mixing bowl and fill box with flour; don't pack it down.

title: recipe for a happy family
directions: Mix thoroughly and sprinkle with awareness.
Bake in moderate oven of everyday life, using fuel all the grudges and past unpleasantness.
Cool.
Turn out onto a platter of cheerfulness. Garnish with tears and laughter.
Serve God and country and community.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine in 2-quart bowl.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs. Add pumpkin. Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture. Add water. Pour into loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour. It also can be baked in 4 smaller loaf pans or 3 regular size pans (5 x 9-inches).

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well and put in casserole dish.
Top with mixture of light brown sugar, flour, oleo and chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 x 10-inch Pyrex.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3 tablespoons warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add sugar, shortening, eggs, 1 cup warm water, salt and 2 cups flour.
Beat at low speed with an electric mixer for 1 minute.
