Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface; knead 4 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Shape dough into a ball, and place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.

title: chicken curry croquettes(makes 16)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour. Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add remaining ingredients, except eggs.
Stir in eggs.
Heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Spread in 8 or 9-inch pie pan, lined with foil.
Freeze 1 1/2 to 2 hours until partially frozen.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients over low heat.
Cool slightly, then fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into the pie shell and refrigerate.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix fruit juices in punch bowl.
Add fruit slices.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Add frozen strawberries in place of ice. Yield:
20 cups.

title: hot wings
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Heat thoroughly.
Cook chicken wings (bake, broil or fry; do not season).
Coat with mixture; place on cookie sheet.
Heat for 5 to 10 minutes at 350° until hot!

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on High for 8 to 10 hours.
During the last half of the cooking time, remove lid and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Makes 5 pints.

title: ham barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together in large saucepan.
Simmer to thicken; add meat until heated through.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Put beef in glass cake pan (8 1/2 x 11); spread sour cream on top of ground beef, put salsa on top of sour cream, then add diced lettuce, diced tomatoes and top with shredded cheese.
It can be eaten warm or you can refrigerate and eat cold.
Just grab the tortilla chips and start dippin.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt oil and brown beef.
Add onions and garlic; pour off excess fat.
Add beans, soup, salt, water, chili powder, vinegar and pepper.
Stir well.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Serve with cornbread or rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in oleo.
Add to crumbs and rest of ingredients.
Add broth from turkey.
Mix well.
Add salt, if needed.
Bake at 350° until done.
Do not overbake.

title: date sticks
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until done, in a 9-inch greased square pan.

title: molasses gingerbread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add the molasses and oil to the dry ingredients and mix well.
Then add the hot water and egg and beat combined ingredients well.
Pour mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add carrots, oil and eggs; beat until well mixed.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Pour batter into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or one 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake for approximately 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove cakes from the oven and allow to cool. When completely cool, top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, blending well. Drop by teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry fruit pie(contains 40 calories)
directions: Spray 9-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl until dissolved; add ice cubes and stir until melted.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into pie plate.
Sprinkle edges with graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or until firm.
Makes 8 servings, 1 fruit exchange.

title: chinese hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add remaining ingredients except Chinese noodles.
Bake in a 350° oven 1 hour.
Remove cover and add Chinese noodles on top; bake 30 minutes longer.

title: kathryn's artichoke dip
directions: Mix all and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle top with grated Velveeta.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until melted and hot. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: savory rice pie with hamburger crust
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, onion, green pepper, oregano, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Pat mixture firmly over bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Roll chops in flour, pepper and celery salt.
Arrange chops in shallow baking dish.
Top with pineapple slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then baste with 1 tablespoon water.
Return to oven until done.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs together.
Add the dry ingredients; blend in milk.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet; press with sugared glass.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: anne's party punch
directions: You can always enhance this punch with vodka or gin.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and water in a bowl; beat for 5 minutes. Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Pour in about 3/4 of the cake batter. Then combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans; sprinkle over the batter in pan. Add the remaining batter and bake for 1 hour on 350°. Let cool for 15 minutes before taking it out the pan.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar in small saucepan over heat, stirring until dissolved.
Remove from heat; pour over rest of ingredients and stir gently to mix well.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients.
Put in a large 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine potato chips with cheese and almonds; sprinkle on top.
Chill overnight.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until very hot.

title: meat loaf hero
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients.
Spread on French bread, which has been split lengthwise.
Wrap in foil and bake 30 minutes in 400° oven.
Remove foil and place cheese on top and cook 5 minutes more.

title: granddaddy's irish stew
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Sprinkle meat with pepper and flour.
Brown in hot skillet in vegetable oil.
Add a small amount of water; cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: north shore potatoes
directions: Refrigerate cooked potatoes for 24 hours.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter with cheese in double boiler.
Add sour cream, salt, pepper and onion.
Stir to blend.
Remove from heat.
Peel cold potatoes; grate and stir into cheese mixture.
Put in oblong pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Good with baked ham!

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth.
Serve as a dip with sliced apples.

title: carrots and broccoli with horseradish sauce
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; cook over low heat until hot (do not boil), stirring constantly.
To serve, spoon about 2 tablespoons sauce on each plate; arrange warm carrots and broccoli on sauce.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: tuna shoe string salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: stir-fry asparagus
directions: Stir-fry asparagus, onion and garlic in butter until tender in large nonstick skillet about 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat.
Gives 4 to 5 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and mix with eggs, margarine and Parmesan cheese.
Shape into crust in buttered pan.
Cook ground beef and onion.
Add tomato, garlic and sugar.
Cook 20 minutes.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti, then top with meat and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and press into buttered loaf pan. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with tomato sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: awesome and easy cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Pat into pie pan.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, vanilla, salt and eggs.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until firm.
Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over hot, baked cheesecake. Bake 10 minutes longer.
Cool.
Refrigerate.
Can be served with fruit topping.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Layer ingredients on a large platter:
refried beans with taco seasoning mixed in, sour cream, avocado dip, chilies, olives, tomato and 2 kinds of cheese.

title: texas jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in jam and preserves.
Stir together dry ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk to jam mixture.
Turn into 3 well-greased wax paper-lined 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Frost with Maple Frosting.
Garnish with nuts if desired.

title: grandma's date pinwheels
directions: Combine dates,
sugar
and
water in pan; cook over low heat until
thick;
about
minutes.
Cream shortening; add brown sugar
and
well
beaten eggs.
Beat well; add remaining ingredients.
Chill
thoroughly.
Divide into 2 parts and roll separately to less than 1/4-inch thick.
Spread each with date filling and
roll.
Chill overnight.
Cut into 1/4-inch thick. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Lay chicken breast halves on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay a slice of cheese on each breast.
Mix soup with 1 cup water and pour over chicken.
Mix seasoned crumbs with melted butter.
Cover all with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini and rice
directions: Peel zucchini; cut in slices, then quarters.
Put oil or Pam in frying pan, then zucchini.
Cover and stir occasionally until soft, then add salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Make rice in another pan. Mix together.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
You can top with cheese and put into oven for a few minutes.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate.
Pour into pan.
Freeze and cut into squares.
Dip in Nestle melted chocolate.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and sugar thoroughly.
Shape into small balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate mix.
It helps to chill the balls before dipping in hot chocolate.
It sets faster.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Grease pan.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Check cake in about 30 minutes.

title: ray's pasta e fagili
directions: Combine oil, onion, Italian seasoning, pepper, parsley, garlic and 1/2 c. water.
Simmer until onion is clarified.
Add tomato sauce, tomato soup, beans, butter and 4 c. water.
Cook pasta and add to sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes, let stand for 10 minutes, and then serve.
Add grated cheese for flavor.

title: cashew and noodle casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in oil or margarine.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together all ingredients.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Cover with foil. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 to 15 more minutes until golden brown.
You can prepare the night before; refrigerate and then bake the next day.

title: margaret's hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Add sugar, condensed milk, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Mix well or beat thoroughly.
Serve over ice cream cake.

title: cheddar pennies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into rolls about one inch in diameter.
Wrap
in
foil
and freeze. When ready to use, slice the roll into 1/8-inch rounds.	Place on greased cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix mayonnaise, butter and cream cheese together well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: kielbasa stir-fry
directions: Brown kielbasa in large, deep skillet or wok (using oil) over medium heat.
Add onions, garlic, green peppers and mushrooms. Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables and stir small amount of cornstarch into chicken broth (for thickening) before adding.
Season to taste.
Allow to simmer for 15 to 30 minutes on low heat.
Serve hot over rice or noodles or alone.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and soda and add alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done when tested.
Cool for 25 minutes in pan.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Saute onions; mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pig lickin cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked apricots
directions: Layer 1/2 of apricots, brown sugar and cracker crumbs in order given in a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Dot with butter. Repeat layers.
Bake in a 300° oven for one hour.
Serves 8.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole which has been lightly greased; do not stir.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sarah's favorite glazed carrots(microwave)
directions: Slice carrots thinly into 1 1/2-inch strips.
Place brown sugar, butter, water, cinnamon and nutmeg into 1 1/2-quart microwavable dish and microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, until butter is melted.
Add sliced carrots and toss to coat evenly with brown sugar mixture.
Cover and microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes, until carrots are tender.

title: oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine and coat bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together. Pour into pan.
Bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: teri sticks
directions: Slice steaks diagonally into 2 x 1 x 1/4-inch strips.
Combine all ingredients.
Marinate meat slices for 30 minutes.
Thread on skewers.
Barbecue or broil until done.
Makes 48.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown onions and beef.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms and simmer. Don't rinse noodles when you drain.
Melt Old English cheese with noodles. Put on low heat if needed.
Mix noodles and sauce mixture.
Top with sharp cheese (shredded).
Bake at 350° for half an hour.

title: portuguese bread
directions: Mix together Bisquick, flour and yeast.
Mix until you can lift your hand without any dough sticking to your fingers.
Place a pinch of dough in a glass of water.
After it rises to the top of glass, knead dough a little.
Take a little dough at a time and shape into little loaves of bread.
Place a pinch of dough into glass again.
When it rises, put bread in oven.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: california chicken
directions: Mix soups and water together.
Add rice.
Pour into baking dish.
Arrange pieces of chicken on top of the mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: french hamburgers
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in bowl.
Spread evenly over bun halves, covering completely.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 6 sandwiches.

title: western hash
directions: Brown beef; add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese slices.
Heat until melted.
Serves 6.

title: apricot pork chops
directions: Drain apricots reserving 1/4 cup syrup; cut apricots in half.

title: homemade italian manicotti(melts in your mouth; worth the effort and fun.)
directions: Beat together milk and 1 egg. Then add flour (enough to get a thin pancake consistency). Fry thin pancakes in oil brushed on thinly for each pancake.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, cheese, flour and 3 tablespoons pineapple juice until well blended.
Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole.

title: chicken with beef
directions: Debone uncooked chicken and wrap each half in a slice of bacon and layer in a pan lined with chopped, dried beef (rinse beef before chopping). Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Do not cover.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: golden clam cakes
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix beaten eggs with chopped clams and stir into flour mixture until thoroughly combined.
Measure the clam juice; add enough water to equal 1 1/2 cups.
Gradually stir into clam mixture to form a slightly thick batter that will fall easily from a spoon.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Mix all together in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Delicious on ice cream.

title: lily coates' lemon cheese
directions: Grate finely only the yellow rind on all 8 lemons.
Ream juice from all 8 lemons.
Put rind, juice, sugar and butter/oleo into top of double boiler and stir until all sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil and slowly add the beaten eggs, whisking constantly so eggs do not congeal.
Stir until thick like pudding.
Remove from heat.
Makes 5 pints.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs all at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Put dry ingredients in bowl.
Add cream mix.
Alternate with sour cream.
Beat after each one is added.
Add flavoring last.

title: angel wings(chrusciki)
directions: Add salt and vanilla to eggs and beat until thick; add lemon juice, sugar and sour cream and continue to beat.
Fold in flour and knead until dough blisters.
Roll dough out very thin and cut into strips about 4-inches long.
Slit each piece in the center and pull one end through the slit.
Fry in hot fat, 350° to 400°, until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mrs. m. l. mahone's eggplant casserole
directions: Pour sauce over eggplant; put into 350° oven and cook until cheese melts well.
Cook in pan of water.

title: fat-free brownies
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Bake about 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Do not overcook!
(Test doneness by inserting fork.
It should come out slightly "gooey".)

title: bread pudding with whiskey sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and set aside. Break bread into chunks, dropping them into a bowl. Pour milk over them. When bread has softened, crumble into small bits and let soak until all the milk is absorbed. In a small bowl, beat 3 eggs and 1 cup of sugar until the mixture is smooth and thick. Stir in raisins, vanilla, nutmeg and cinnamon. Pour over the bread crumbs and stir until all the ingredients are well combined. Pour the bread pudding into baking dish. Place the dish in a large shallow roasting pan set in the middle of oven. Add water to the roasting pan to a depth of 1-inch. Bake 1 hour or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: cocktail wieners and sauce
directions: Heat chili sauce, jelly, lemon juice and sugar until jelly dissolves.
Add wieners and simmer in crock pot.

title: pepper steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper on a plate. Cut steak in 1/2-inch strips. Coat thoroughly with mixture and brown in oil in a large skillet. Add tomato sauce, water, onion, garlic and bouillon cube. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover; stir in Worcestershire sauce and green pepper. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss with dressing: 1 c. mayonnaise, 1/2 c. sugar, and 1 tsp. vinegar. It is best to prepare dressing first and allow to marinate.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order given; chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat first three ingredients to soft peaks.
Add sugar gradually while beating very stiff.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Turn off oven when you put cookies in oven and leave in oven overnight. Remove in morning.
Makes about 40.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly (reserve 1 cup).
Pat remaining mixture lightly in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and fluffy.
Spread over baked layer. Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: quick pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy with electric mixer. Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour gradually and mix at low speed. Grease and flour a tube pan.
Pour mixture into pan and cook in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: whoppin' butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and vanilla at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add flour and 1 cup crushed malted balls at low speed.

title: marshmallow delight
directions: Cut marshmallows fine with scissors.
Add pineapple.
Stir lightly and chill 3 hours.
One hour before serving, add 1/2 pint whipping cream.
Fold in lightly.
Serve with whipping cream and a cherry on top.
Should be served in fancy glasses.

title: quick and easy apple dumplings
directions: Cut apple into 8 pieces.
Roll each apple piece into a slice of crescent roll and place in an 8x8-inch baking dish.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and pour over crackers. Blend well.
Dry on paper towel.
"Enjoy".

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake as regular cornbread.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to dry ingredients and add milk.
Mix well. Roll to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with round biscuit cutter.
Dip biscuits in melted butter and fold in half.
Bake on cookie sheet in a 400° oven for 15 minutes or until brown.
Half a package of yeast (1 1/2 teaspoons) will make half a batch.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes about 20 minutes; drain, cool and peel.
Cut in half lengthwise.
In large skillet, stir sugar, margarine and syrup.
Arrange potatoes on top (cut side down).
Cook over low heat basting occasionally or until potatoes are well glazed.

title: the world's best cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour and oil. Blend in other ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°. Cool cookies on paper towels.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add brown sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla, then add flour gradually, mixing well.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Combine ingredients in order and pour into pie shells. Bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes or inset knife and if it comes out clean, it's done. When cool, garnish with whipped cream if desired.

title: stuffed pasta shell salad
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
In shallow glass or stainless steel bowl (not aluminum) combine macaroni shells and dressing.
Toss to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap and let marinate in refrigerator until chilled. In small bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Using slotted spoon remove shells from bowl, reserving dressing.
Spoon 1/8 of cheese mixture into each shell. Set shells on serving platter and drizzle with reserved dressing.

title: chicken scallopini
directions: Cut chicken breast halves crosswise into 4 pieces.
Place between 2 pieces of waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Pound until 1/4-inch thick.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; cook and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into blender container and process until smooth.
Serve with shrimp, oysters, lobsters and/or crab.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: crock-pot pot roast
directions: Chop the onion and the garlic.
Put the onion and garlic in the crock-pot and set the roast on top.
Sprinkle with the salt, pepper, rosemary and thyme.
Pour in the wine.
Cover and cook on the high setting until the meat is very tender, about 5 hours. Remove the roast to a serving plate.
Measure 2 cups of the cooking liquid into a saucepan.
Stir together the flour and water and stir it into the cooking liquid.
Bring to a boil, stirring. Reduce the heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Slice the roast and serve with the gravy.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients; put in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: braised chicken(serves 4)
directions: Dredge chicken with flour; shake off.
Heat oil and butter; saute onions and mushrooms 5 to 7 minutes until soft.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Brown meat on both sides and remove.
Add wine to deglaze, then broth.
Return meat and vegetables.
Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with sauce.

title: quick dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add flour (plain, all-purpose) until the thickness of biscuit dough.
Place in refrigerator for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and knead until thickness of biscuit dough.
Roll about the thickness of biscuits.
Have pan buttered.
Place rolls in pan; brush with melted butter or margarine.
Let set for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Put in oven at 400° until golden brown and brush with melted butter again.
Remove from pan gently. Double recipe for larger amount, except add 3 packages of yeast.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Place the ingredients in large mixing bowl and blend good, then transfer to a oiled baking dish and let it sit in a cool place for about 30 minutes so that the meat will absorb the seasoning.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
If you wish, lay 2 or 3 slices of bacon over the loaf before putting it into the oven.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press in a flat pan.

title: country ham with red-eye gravy
directions: Make cuts in fat to keep ham from curling. Melt butter over low heat in a heavy skillet; add ham and cook 5 minutes on each side or until browned. Remove ham from skillet and keep warm. Stir brown sugar into hot drippings until dissolved, if desired. Add coffee and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Serve with ham or with ham and biscuits. Yields 1 cup gravy.

title: garden relish
directions: Chop vegetables and combine.
Add salt.
Mix; drain and squeeze gently.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over drained vegetables.
Bring ingredients to a boil and seal in hot Mason jars.

title: basgne fish soup
directions: In large saucepan or pot, saute onion, celery and garlic in butter or margarine.
Cut up tomatoes and add to pan with wine, parsley, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add fish and simmer 7 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Sprinkle with extra parsley and serve with green salad and crusty bread.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: "last minute" cookies
directions: Melt butter slightly in the microwave.
Add sugar and cream, then eggs and beat well. Add the flour, baking powder and salt. Add the milk and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork dipped in sugar and sprinkle a little more sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes until light golden brown around the edges.
You can bake these 1/2 hour before you dash off to a meeting and everyone will love these soft, super good cookies.
If you have a little more time, chill the dough and it is good rolled out and cut with cookie cutters.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all together, except last 3 ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan; let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Take out 1 1/2 hours before placing in oven.
Top with buttered bread crumbs before baking.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop cauliflower, broccoli, onion and lettuce in a large bowl. Mix with cheese and Ranch dressing and top with bacon (crumbled).

title: chill out with gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients in an appropriate container.
Chill 24 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place butter in an 8-inch square baking dish. Place dish in oven at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes or until butter melts. Combine flour and sugar in a medium bowl; add milk and almond extract, stirring until smooth.

Pour batter over melted butter. (Do not stir.) Pour blackberries over batter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until golden. Serve warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream. Makes 6 servings.

title: angel food candy
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and vinegar. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves. Cook without stirring until the candy thermometer reaches 300° (hard-crack stage). Do not overcook. Remove from heat and quickly stir in baking soda (mixture will foam). Pour immediately into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch metal pan. Do not spread as the mixture will not fill the pan. When cool, break into bite-sized pieces. Dip into favorite chocolate coating and place on waxed paper until the coating is firm. Store candy in tightly covered containers. Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli ham stromboli
directions: Flatten out dough on 12 x 15-inch rectangular baking stone/pan. Brush with mustard to taste.
Lay down 1/2 of the ham slices. Combine mushrooms, cheese, onion and broccoli; spread mixture on top of ham slices.
Use garlic press to press 2 cloves of garlic over mixture.
Layer with remaining ham.
Bring sides of dough together and close ends.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Thin soup with milk (can double soup and milk for more sauce).
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with melted butter. Spoon over soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: gramona's rice and tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 quart casserole with Pam.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Bake 20 minutes. Remove from oven; cover with cheese slices.
Sprinkle with chips or crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes more or until cheese is melted.

title: "cheddar" stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut prebaked potatoes in half.
Spoon out center of potatoes being careful not to break shells.
Blend yogurt, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese and dill weed until smooth but not creamy using an electric mixer or fork.
Add green onion. Spoon mixture into potato shells.
Sprinkle tops with paprika. Place in oven for 15 to 20 minutes until heated throughout.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix first 9
ingredients in order given.
Spread half batter in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add rhubarb and spread remainder of batter over the top.
Sprinkle with white sugar mixed with cinnamon over it and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix and pie filling together.
Spread into jelly roll or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
You may dust with powdered sugar or cover with a lemon glaze.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 400° in iron skillet or in 8 x 8-inch square pan for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; cool.
Peel and slice 1/4-inch thick slices.
Peel and core apples.
Slice into 1/4-inch thick rings.
Butter a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put 1/2 the potatoes on bottom, then apples, then rest of potatoes on top.
Combine the rest of ingredients.
Pour over potatoes and apples.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt over medium heat until mixture dissolves. Add the peanuts. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook until peanuts turn brown; it will take 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from heat and add the soda. Spread mixture over foil or greased dish.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Prepare bacon in skillet over medium heat; drain and crumble. In large pot, combine potato patties, water and bouillon cubes. Cover and place over medium-low heat until patties are thawed and crumbled.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients in order listed. Stir until ingredients are well blended.
Cover and cook over low heat about 20 minutes, or until carrots are tender and soup is hot.
Do not allow soup to boil.

title: christmas cutout cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Roll out and cut into desired shapes.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Ice and decorate cookies.
Best to let dough chill before rolling out. Makes 4 dozen.

title: pineapple open-face tarts
directions: Combine pineapple, brown sugar, corn starch and salt.
Cook over low heat until thickened and clear, about 5 to 8 minutes. Stir in butter.
Cool.
Spoon into baked tart shells and top with whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: melva's chili
directions: In Dutch oven, heat oil and fry steak and ground meat quickly. When tender, add onion and garlic and cook until onions are tender. Stir in rest of ingredients, except beans.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add beans, if desired; simmer for another 30 minutes.
